{"title_page": "Vishwamitra (1995 TV Series)", "text_new": "'''''Vishwamitra''''' is an Indian mythological television series, which aired during 1995, produced and directed by [[Dasari Narayana Rao]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Vishwamitra|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0262876/|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> The dialogues for the show were written by the Urdu poet [[Rahi Masoom Raza]] who previously wrote dialogues for [[Mahabharat (1988 TV series)|Mahabharat (1988 TV series).]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deepawali.co.in/vishwamitra-serial-doordarshan-hindi-%e0%a4%b5%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%b6%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%b5%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%ae%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%a4%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%b0-%e0%a4%b8%e0%a5%80%e0%a4%b0%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%af%e0%a4%b2.html|title=\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930 \u0913\u0932\u094d\u0921 \u0926\u0942\u0930\u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u091f\u0940 \u0935\u0940 \u0938\u0940\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0932 {{!}} Vishwamitra Old Doordarshan Serial In hindi|last=\u0921\u093f\u091c\u093e\u0908\u0928|first=Ankita\u0905\u0902\u0915\u093f\u0924\u093e \u0926\u0940\u092a\u093e\u0935\u0932\u0940 \u0915\u0940|last2=\u0939\u0948{{!}}|first2=\u0921\u0947\u0935\u0932\u092a\u092e\u0947\u0902\u091f \u0914\u0930 \u0906\u0930\u094d\u091f\u093f\u0915\u0932 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0930\u094d\u091a \u0907\u0902\u091c\u0928 \u0915\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u0947\u0937\u0917\u094d\u092f \u0939\u0948{{!}} \u092f\u0947 \u0907\u0938 \u0938\u093e\u0908\u091f \u0915\u0940 \u090f\u0921\u092e\u093f\u0928 \u0939\u0948{{!}} \u0907\u0928\u0915\u094b \u0935\u0947\u092c\u0938\u093e\u0907\u091f \u0911\u092a\u094d\u091f\u093f\u092e\u093e\u0907\u091c\u093c \u0914\u0930 \u0915\u092d\u0940 \u0915\u092d\u0940 \u0906\u0930\u094d\u091f\u093f\u0915\u0932 \u0932\u093f\u0916\u0928\u093e \u092a\u0938\u0902\u0926|date=2016-11-11|website=Deepawali|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0925\u093e \u092d\u093e\u0917 1 - \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u0916\u0928\u094d\u0928\u093e, \u0905\u0930\u0941\u0923 \u0917\u094b\u0935\u093f\u0932 - Vishwamitra Katha|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GOInQn_C0hk|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2l01x1|title=Vishwamitra Title Track - Doordarshan National (DD1) - video dailymotion|website=Dailymotion|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dla.library.upenn.edu/dla/vcat/record.html?id=VCAT_3761598&|title=Vishwamitra (1995)|website=dla.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Vishwamitra-Set-DVDs-Complete-T-V/dp/B00F3B1IY8|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://franklin.library.upenn.edu/catalog/FRANKLIN_9937615983503681|title=Vishwamitra|date=c2002.|website=franklin.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThe show had its original run on [[DD National]]. \n\n== Cast ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Actor\n!Character\n|-\n|Mukesh Khanna\n|[[Vishvamitra|Vishwamitra]] / Vishwarath \n|-\n|Arun Govil\n|Raja [[Harishchandra]]\n|-\n|[[Arvind Trivedi]] \n|Sathyavrata ([[Trishanku]])\n|-\n|[[Mulraj Rajda]]\n|Vashishtha \n|-\n|[[Bhanupriya]]\n|[[Menaka]]\n|-\n|[[Virendra Razdan]]\n|[[Kanva|Rishi Kanva]]\n|-\n|[[Shantipriya (actress)|Shantipriya]]\n|[[Shakuntala]]\n|-\n|[[Sudhakar (Telugu actor)|Sudhakar]]\n|Dushyanta\n|-\n|[[Mohan Choti]]\n|Nakshatrik\n|}\n\n== Plot  ==\nThe story of show follows the character of Kshatriya King Vishwarath becoming a Brahmarishi Vishwamitra the sage after a feud with Sage Vashishtha over the divine cow '''Nandini'''.\n\n<br />\n== Episodes ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!No.\n!Notes\n|-\n|1\n|Vishwarath anointed as the new King by his father.\n|-\n|2\n|He reaches [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s [[ashram]] with his army after a war. After getting exceptional hospitality in the ashram, he came to know about the divine cow Nandini. When a famine struck his kingdom he asks his counsel to get Nandini cow from [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]], which the later refuses.\n|-\n|3\n|Angry King Vishwarath reaches the ashram and tries to get the cow forcefully but failed. The humiliated king decides to gain divine power by doing [[Tapas (Indian religions)|tapasya]] and abdicates the throne for his son.\n|-\n|4\n|Vishwarath got the boon of various divine weapons from [[Brahma|Lord Brahma]]. He again reaches [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s [[ashram]] to capture Nandini but fails. He vows to gain more power by doing great penance to become a [[Brahmarshi|Brahmarishi]].\n|-\n|5\n|Ayodhya King Sathyavrata anoints his son Harishchandra as the new King and decides to ascend heaven with his mortal body. However, his unnatural wishes got refuted by [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]. He tried to lure [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s son Satya to help him achieve his desires. An angry Satya curses Sathyavrata and makes him [[Trishanku]].\n|-\n|6\n|Vishwarath after severe penance and tapasya gained more powers and blessing of Mother Gayatri, Vishwarath the warrior became Vishwamitra the sage.\n|-\n|7\n|A dejected [[Trishanku]] approaches Vishwamitra to achieve his desires. After knowing that [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] refused his wishes, Vishwamitra promises him the impossible. But his [[yajna]] got rejected by Indra and other gods.\n|-\n|8\n|Vishwamitra begins creating alternate heaven for Trishanku when gods dismiss him from Indra's heaven.\n|-\n|9\n|[[B\u1e5bhaspati]] (along with [[Narada]] ) tries to persuade Vishwamitra to abandon creation new heaven for Trishanku which he agrees. However, Narada later instigates him reminding the promise he made to Trishanku. Vishwamitra begins more penance to gain uninterrupted access to heaven. Knowing this Indra and other gods (on the advice of Brhaspati) decide to disrupt his [[tapasya]]. They create a celestial Mahashakti after uniting their powers. But he failed and Vishwamitra killed him with his divine powers.\n|-\n|10\n|[[Indra]] decides to disrupt Vishwamitra's penance by sending [[apsara]] Rambha to seduce him. But an angry Vishwamitra curses her and turned her into a rock. She regretted her actions and asked for forgiveness. He gave her the boon that in future she will be liberated by a Maharishi. After failing repeatedly, Indra decides to disrupt his tapasya himself and went to Vishwamitra disguising as a hungry brahmin. But Vishwamitra recognized him easily and still gave his divine food gained from penance. He embarrasses Indra for his malevolent deeds. A dejected and humiliated Indra leaves for heaven.\n|-\n|11\n|Upon advice of Brhaspati, Indra summons apsara [[Menaka|Meneka]] to seduce Vishwamitra. A reluctant Menaka agrees for the task. She decides to take help from [[Rati]] and [[Kamadeva|Kamadev]].\n|-\n|12\n|After severe attempts Menaka successfully gained the attention of Vishwamitra and made him fell in love with her. \n|-\n|13\n|Both of them got married and thus Indra task finally got fulfilled. He then asks Menaka to return back to heaven but Menaka refuses as she's in love with Vishwamitra too. Indra orders her to return as it'll be unnatural for a celestial being to spend time on earth. A year later Menaka gave birth to a daughter. Narada reminds Indra that Menaka hasn't returned to heaven. \n|-\n|14\n|Menaka finally confesses to Vishwamitra that she was sent on a mission by Indra and now as her task is complete she had to return. An angry and disheartened Vishwamitra abandons Menaka and his daughter and sets out to fulfill his vow to become a Maharishi. Menaka also ascended to heaven leaving their daughter behind. [[Rishi]] [[Kanva]] and his wife Gautami found the girl in the forest and adopted her. As a baby, she was surrounded by Shakunta birds ([[Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]]: \u0936\u0915\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0924, \u015bakunta). Therefore, he named her Shakuntala (Sanskrit: \u0936\u0915\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0932\u093e), meaning Shakunta-protected.\n|-\n|15\n|King [[Dushyanta]] arrives in Rishi Kanva's ashram and fell in love with Shakuntala.\n|-\n|16\n|Shakuntala and Dushyant's love blossoms.\n|-\n|17\n|Dushyant proposes Shakuntala for marriage and they have a [[gandharva]] marriage. Having to leave after some time, Dushyant gives Shakuntala a royal ring as a sign of their love, promising her that he will come to her. One day, sage [[Durvasa]] visits the hermitage, but Shakuntala, who is too absorbed in her love for Dushyant, forgets to serve him food. In a fit of anger, sage Durvasa curses her, saying that the person she is thinking about will forget her.\n|-\n|18\n|Shocked friends of Shakuntala begs for forgiveness and the sage, after recollecting his calm, assures her that the person will remember her again when she shows some proof of their acquaintance. Her friends decide not to tell her anything about the curse. Shakuntala got pregnant and Rishi Kanva decides to send her to Dushyanta. \n|-\n|19\n|So, Shakuntala sets off to the capital, [[Hastinapur]], to remind Dushyant of their past love. Dushyanta does not recollect Shakuntala and asks for proof but an accident occurs by which a fish consumes the royal ring, leaving Shakuntala with no formidable proof. A disheartened Shakuntala left the capital. Her mother Menaka helped her and took her to a sage's ashram so that she can give birth to the child. A fisherman brought the lost ring back to the King and his memory and love are rekindled.\n|-\n|20\n|Meanwhile, Shakuntala gave birth to [[Bharata (Mahabharata)|Bharata]]. One day King Dushyanta while hunting met Bharata & Shakuntala, and the couple is finally reunited. A meeting is called in heaven by Indra with combine participation of representatives of earth and heaven. All [[Brahmarshi|Brahmarishis]] are invited and [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] urges Indra to call Maharishi Vishwamitra too as he'll be soon a Brahamrishi. Narada is asked to invite Vishwamitra which he accepts. During the meeting, a discussion arises about the most valuable matter in the universe. [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] concluded that there is nothing more precious than truth. He also named Raja [[Harishchandra]] as the king who follows the difficult path of truth. His claim is challenged by Vishwamitra and he proposes to test Harishchandra's integrity. \n|-\n|21\n|To assess Harishchandra's commitment towards truthfulness, Vishwamitra reaches his court and asks for an unusually huge amount of treasure for yajna purpose which the King readily accepts. Even upon insistence from the King and his counsel, Vishwamitra refuses to take the treasure at once and asks the king to set aside the treasure with himself and he will take it when the right time arrives. Later, Viswamitra creates and send wild animals to Harishchandra's kingdom to further test his mettle. Harishchandra saves his subject from wild animals.\n|-\n|22\n|Using his powers, Vishwamitra creates two Matangi girls and send them to seduce Raja Harishchandra. The girls are not able to seduce Harishchandra. He is rather disgusted with their seductive performance and asked them to leave with some rewards. But the girls refused to take any reward and in turn ask the King to marry them. Harishchandra refuses to marry them as he is already married to Taramati. The girls then offered themselves as concubines which he vehemently refuses. Later a furious Vishwamitra arrives in Harishchandra's court over the rejection of his magical daughters. Even after the strong insistence of Vishwamitra, Harishchandra refuses to marry his daughters and decides to relinquish his kingdom for saving dharma. He hands over his entire kingdom to Vishwamitra but when he prepares to leaves for Kashi with his wife and son, Vishwamitra asks for the money promised to him for yajna purpose. Harishchandra asks for a month's time to fulfill the promise. Vishwamitra sends his disciple Nakshatrik to accompany them.\n|-\n|23\n|On his journey to Kashi, Vishwamitra creates many hurdles to deviate Harishchandra from dharma. He creates Mayamuni to misguide Harishchandra from the correct path. Vishwamitra's disciple Nakshatrik also keeps giving a hard time to Harishchandra throughout his journey. Vishwamitra creates a Betaal to scare Harishchandra and his family at night but Harishchandra kills him in a duel. Finally, they reach Kashi and Nakshatrik asks for the promised money. Unable to pay anything, Harishchandra asks for some time but Nakshatrik gives him the choice to back-out from his words as there is no way he can deliver his commitment. Taramati asks his husband to sell her off as a slave so that he can pay the money to Vishwamitra. A reluctant Harishchandra agrees for it.\n|-\n|24\n|\n|}\n\n== Music ==\nLyrics for various songs were written by Bhring Tupkari and music was composed by Vasu Rao. The title song was performed by [[K. J. Yesudas|Yesudas]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dla.library.upenn.edu/dla/vcat/record.html?id=VCAT_3761598&rotation=0&detail=staff|title=Vishwamitra (1995)|website=dla.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n<br />\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0262876}}\n\n\n[[Category:Indian mythological television series]]\n[[Category:1995 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Doordarshan television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n", "text_old": "'''''Vishwamitra''''' is an Indian mythological television series, which aired during 1995, produced and directed by [[Dasari Narayana Rao]].<ref>{{Citation|title=Vishwamitra|url=http://www.imdb.com/title/tt0262876/|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref> The dialogues for the show were written by the Urdu poet [[Rahi Masoom Raza]] who previously wrote dialogues for [[Mahabharat (1988 TV series)|Mahabharat (1988 TV series).]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.deepawali.co.in/vishwamitra-serial-doordarshan-hindi-%e0%a4%b5%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%b6%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%b5%e0%a4%be%e0%a4%ae%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%a4%e0%a5%8d%e0%a4%b0-%e0%a4%b8%e0%a5%80%e0%a4%b0%e0%a4%bf%e0%a4%af%e0%a4%b2.html|title=\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930 \u0913\u0932\u094d\u0921 \u0926\u0942\u0930\u0926\u0930\u094d\u0936\u0928 \u091f\u0940 \u0935\u0940 \u0938\u0940\u0930\u093f\u092f\u0932 {{!}} Vishwamitra Old Doordarshan Serial In hindi|last=\u0921\u093f\u091c\u093e\u0908\u0928|first=Ankita\u0905\u0902\u0915\u093f\u0924\u093e \u0926\u0940\u092a\u093e\u0935\u0932\u0940 \u0915\u0940|last2=\u0939\u0948{{!}}|first2=\u0921\u0947\u0935\u0932\u092a\u092e\u0947\u0902\u091f \u0914\u0930 \u0906\u0930\u094d\u091f\u093f\u0915\u0932 \u0915\u0947 \u0938\u0930\u094d\u091a \u0907\u0902\u091c\u0928 \u0915\u0940 \u0935\u093f\u0936\u0947\u0937\u0917\u094d\u092f \u0939\u0948{{!}} \u092f\u0947 \u0907\u0938 \u0938\u093e\u0908\u091f \u0915\u0940 \u090f\u0921\u092e\u093f\u0928 \u0939\u0948{{!}} \u0907\u0928\u0915\u094b \u0935\u0947\u092c\u0938\u093e\u0907\u091f \u0911\u092a\u094d\u091f\u093f\u092e\u093e\u0907\u091c\u093c \u0914\u0930 \u0915\u092d\u0940 \u0915\u092d\u0940 \u0906\u0930\u094d\u091f\u093f\u0915\u0932 \u0932\u093f\u0916\u0928\u093e \u092a\u0938\u0902\u0926|date=2016-11-11|website=Deepawali|language=en-US|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Citation|title=\u0935\u093f\u0936\u094d\u0935\u093e\u092e\u093f\u0924\u094d\u0930 \u0915\u0940 \u0915\u0925\u093e \u092d\u093e\u0917 1 - \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u0916\u0928\u094d\u0928\u093e, \u0905\u0930\u0941\u0923 \u0917\u094b\u0935\u093f\u0932 - Vishwamitra Katha|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=GOInQn_C0hk|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.dailymotion.com/video/x2l01x1|title=Vishwamitra Title Track - Doordarshan National (DD1) - video dailymotion|website=Dailymotion|language=en|access-date=2020-03-29}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dla.library.upenn.edu/dla/vcat/record.html?id=VCAT_3761598&|title=Vishwamitra (1995)|website=dla.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.amazon.com/Vishwamitra-Set-DVDs-Complete-T-V/dp/B00F3B1IY8|website=www.amazon.com|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://franklin.library.upenn.edu/catalog/FRANKLIN_9937615983503681|title=Vishwamitra|date=c2002.|website=franklin.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-05}}</ref>\n\nThe show had its original run on [[DD National]]. \n\n== Cast ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!Actor\n!Character\n|-\n|Mukesh Khanna\n|[[Vishvamitra|Vishwamitra]] / Vishwarath \n|-\n|Arun Govil\n|Raja [[Harishchandra]]\n|-\n|[[Arvind Trivedi]] \n|Sathyavrata ([[Trishanku]])\n|-\n|[[Mulraj Rajda]]\n|Vashishtha \n|-\n|[[Bhanupriya]]\n|[[Menaka]]\n|-\n|[[Virendra Razdan]]\n|[[Kanva|Rishi Kanva]]\n|-\n|[[Shantipriya (actress)|Shantipriya]]\n|[[Shakuntala]]\n|-\n|[[Sudhakar (Telugu actor)|Sudhakar]]\n|Dushyanta\n|-\n|[[Mohan Choti]]\n|Nakshatrik\n|}\n\n== Plot  ==\nThe story of show follows the character of Kshatriya King Vishwarath becoming a Brahmarishi Vishwamitra the sage after a feud with Sage Vashishtha over the divine cow '''Nandini'''.\n\n<br />\n== Episodes ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+\n!No.\n!Notes\n|-\n|1\n|Vishwarath anointed as the new King by his father.\n|-\n|2\n|He reaches [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s [[ashram]] with his army after a war. After getting exceptional hospitality in the ashram, he came to know about the divine cow Nandini. When a famine struck his kingdom he asks his counsel to get Nandini cow from [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]], which the later refuses.\n|-\n|3\n|Angry King Vishwarath reaches the ashram and tries to get the cow forcefully but failed. The humiliated king decides to gain divine power by doing [[Tapas (Indian religions)|tapasya]] and abdicates the throne for his son.\n|-\n|4\n|Vishwarath got the boon of various divine weapons from [[Brahma|Lord Brahma]]. He again reaches [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s [[ashram]] to capture Nandini but fails. He vows to gain more power by doing great penance to become a [[Brahmarshi|Brahmarishi]].\n|-\n|5\n|Ayodhya King Sathyavrata anoints his son Harishchandra as the new King and decides to ascend heaven with his mortal body. However, his unnatural wishes got refuted by [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]. He tried to lure [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]]'s son Satya to help him achieve his desires. An angry Satya curses Sathyavrata and makes him [[Trishanku]].\n|-\n|6\n|Vishwarath after severe penance and tapasya gained more powers and blessing of Mother Gayatri, Vishwarath the warrior became Vishwamitra the sage.\n|-\n|7\n|A dejected [[Trishanku]] approaches Vishwamitra to achieve his desires. After knowing that [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] refused his wishes, Vishwamitra promises him the impossible. But his [[yajna]] got rejected by Indra and other gods.\n|-\n|8\n|Vishwamitra begins creating alternate heaven for Trishanku when gods dismiss him from Indra's heaven.\n|-\n|9\n|[[B\u1e5bhaspati]] (along with [[Narada]] ) tries to persuade Vishwamitra to abandon creation new heaven for Trishanku which he agrees. However, Narada later instigates him reminding the promise he made to Trishanku. Vishwamitra begins more penance to gain uninterrupted access to heaven. Knowing this Indra and other gods (on the advice of Brhaspati) decide to disrupt his [[tapasya]]. They create a celestial Mahashakti after uniting their powers. But he failed and Vishwamitra killed him with his divine powers.\n|-\n|10\n|[[Indra]] decides to disrupt Vishwamitra's penance by sending [[apsara]] Rambha to seduce him. But an angry Vishwamitra curses her and turned her into a rock. She regretted her actions and asked for forgiveness. He gave her the boon that in future she will be liberated by a Maharishi. After failing repeatedly, Indra decides to disrupt his tapasya himself and went to Vishwamitra disguising as a hungry brahmin. But Vishwamitra recognized him easily and still gave his divine food gained from penance. He embarrasses Indra for his malevolent deeds. A dejected and humiliated Indra leaves for heaven.\n|-\n|11\n|Upon advice of Brhaspati, Indra summons apsara [[Menaka|Meneka]] to seduce Vishwamitra. A reluctant Menaka agrees for the task. She decides to take help from [[Rati]] and [[Kamadeva|Kamadev]].\n|-\n|12\n|After severe attempts Menaka successfully gained the attention of Vishwamitra and made him fell in love with her. \n|-\n|13\n|Both of them got married and thus Indra task finally got fulfilled. He then asks Menaka to return back to heaven but Menaka refuses as she's in love with Vishwamitra too. Indra orders her to return as it'll be unnatural for a celestial being to spend time on earth. A year later Menaka gave birth to a daughter. Narada reminds Indra that Menaka hasn't returned to heaven. \n|-\n|14\n|Menaka finally confesses to Vishwamitra that she was sent on a mission by Indra and now as her task is complete she had to return. An angry and disheartened Vishwamitra abandons Menaka and his daughter and sets out to fulfill his vow to become a Maharishi. Menaka also ascended to heaven leaving their daughter behind. [[Rishi]] [[Kanva]] and his wife Gautami found the girl in the forest and adopted her. As a baby, she was surrounded by Shakunta birds ([[Sanskrit language|Sanskrit]]: \u0936\u0915\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0924, \u015bakunta). Therefore, he named her Shakuntala (Sanskrit: \u0936\u0915\u0941\u0928\u094d\u0924\u0932\u093e), meaning Shakunta-protected.\n|-\n|15\n|King [[Dushyanta]] arrives in Rishi Kanva's ashram and fell in love with Shakuntala.\n|-\n|16\n|Shakuntala and Dushyant's love blossoms.\n|-\n|17\n|Dushyant proposes Shakuntala for marriage and they have a [[gandharva]] marriage. Having to leave after some time, Dushyant gives Shakuntala a royal ring as a sign of their love, promising her that he will come to her. One day, sage [[Durvasa]] visits the hermitage, but Shakuntala, who is too absorbed in her love for Dushyant, forgets to serve him food. In a fit of anger, sage Durvasa curses her, saying that the person she is thinking about will forget her.\n|-\n|18\n|Shocked friends of Shakuntala begs for forgiveness and the sage, after recollecting his calm, assures her that the person will remember her again when she shows some proof of their acquaintance. Her friends decide not to tell her anything about the curse. Shakuntala got pregnant and Rishi Kanva decides to send her to Dushyanta. \n|-\n|19\n|So, Shakuntala sets off to the capital, [[Hastinapur]], to remind Dushyant of their past love. Dushyanta does not recollect Shakuntala and asks for proof but an accident occurs by which a fish consumes the royal ring, leaving Shakuntala with no formidable proof. A disheartened Shakuntala left the capital. Her mother Menaka helped her and took her to a sage's ashram so that she can give birth to the child. A fisherman brought the lost ring back to the King and his memory and love are rekindled.\n|-\n|20\n|Meanwhile, Shakuntala gave birth to [[Bharata (Mahabharata)|Bharata]]. One day King Dushyanta while hunting met Bharata & Shakuntala, and the couple is finally reunited. A meeting is called in heaven by Indra with combine participation of representatives of earth and heaven. All [[Brahmarshi|Brahmarishis]] are invited and [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] urges Indra to call Maharishi Vishwamitra too as he'll be soon a Brahamrishi. Narada is asked to invite Vishwamitra which he accepts. During the meeting, a discussion arises about the most valuable matter in the universe. [[Vasishtha|Vashishtha]] concluded that there is nothing more precious than truth. He also named Raja [[Harishchandra]] as the king who follows the difficult path of truth. His claim is challenged by Vishwamitra and he proposes to test Harishchandra's integrity. \n|-\n|21\n|To assess Harishchandra's commitment towards truthfulness, Vishwamitra reaches his court and asks for an unusually huge amount of treasure for yajna purpose which the King readily accepts. Even upon insistence from the King and his counsel, Vishwamitra refuses to take the treasure at once and asks the king to set aside the treasure with himself and he will take it when the right time arrives. Later, Viswamitra creates and send wild animals to Harishchandra's kingdom to further test his mettle.\n|-\n|22\n|Using his powers, Vishwamitra creates two Matangi girls and send them to seduce Raja Harishchandra's camp. The girls are not able to seduce Harishchandra. He is rather disgusted with their seductive performance and asked them to leave with some rewards. But the girls refused to take any reward and in turn ask the King to marry them. Harishchandra refuses to marry them as he is already married to Taramati. The girls then offered themselves as concubines which he vehemently refuses. Later a furious Vishwamitra arrives in Harishchandra's court over the rejection of his magical daughters. Even after the strong insistence of Vishwamitra, Harishchandra refuses to marry his daughters and decides to relinquish his kingdom for saving dharma. He hands over his entire kingdom to Vishwamitra but when he prepares to leaves for Kashi with his wife and son, Vishwamitra asks for the money promised to him for yajna purpose. Harishchandra asks for a month's time to fulfill the promise. Vishwamitra sends his disciple Nakshatrik to accompany them.\n|-\n|\n|\n|}\n\n== Music ==\nLyrics for various songs were written by Bhring Tupkari and music was composed by Vasu Rao. The title song was performed by [[K. J. Yesudas|Yesudas]]. <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://dla.library.upenn.edu/dla/vcat/record.html?id=VCAT_3761598&rotation=0&detail=staff|title=Vishwamitra (1995)|website=dla.library.upenn.edu|access-date=2020-04-04}}</ref>\n<br />\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n* {{IMDb title|id=0262876}}\n\n\n[[Category:Indian mythological television series]]\n[[Category:1995 Indian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Doordarshan television series]]\n[[Category:Hindi-language television programs]]\n", "name_user": "Unclewalker", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eEpisodes", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Vishwamitra_(1995_TV_Series)"}
{"title_page": "Gisele B\u00fcndchen", "text_new": "{{good article}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use MDY|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n|name        = Gisele B\u00fcndchen\n|image       = Gisele Bundchen-012 (16251942066).jpg\n|caption     = B\u00fcndchen in January 2015\n|birth_name  = Gisele Caroline B\u00fcndchen<ref name=\"PF\"/>\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1980|7|20}}\n|birth_place = [[Horizontina]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Brazil]]\n|occupation={{flatlist|\n* model\n* actress\n* environmental activist\n* businesswoman\n* author\n}}\n|years_active = 1997\u2013present\n|haircolor   = {{flatlist|\n*Light brown<ref name=\"IMG Models\">Per \"Stats\" pulldown at {{cite web|title= Gisele| url=http://imgmodels.com/portfolio/new-york/women/model?mid=21993|publisher=[[IMG Models]]|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref>}}\n|eyecolor    = {{flatlist|\n*Blue<ref name=\"IMG Models\" />}}\n|height      = {{height|m=1.80}}<ref name=\"IMG Models\"/>\n|agency      = [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imgmodels.com/gisele/sydney/women/portfolio|title=Gisele: IMG Models|website=Imgmodels.com|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref><br/>Model Management (Hamburg)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/Gisele-Bundchen|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen - Model|website=Models.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n|website     =\n|spouse      = {{Marriage|[[Tom Brady]]|2009}}\n|children    = 2\n}}\n'''Gisele Caroline B\u00fcndchen'''<ref name=\"PF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lofficielusa.com/fashion/gisele-bundchen-38-birthday-runway-model-moments |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen's Most Iconic Catwalk Moments|publisher=[[L'Officiel]] }}</ref> ({{IPA-pt|\u0292i\u02c8z\u025bli \u02c8b\u0129t\u0283\u1ebd|br}}, {{IPA-de|\u02c8b\u028fnt\u00e7n\u0329|lang}}, born 20 July 1980)<ref name=\"dw2006\">{{Cite news|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: \"Brazil Should Become World Champion\" |url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,,2029705,00.html |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=27 May 2006 |accessdate=3 March 2011 |quote=Gisele B\u00fcndchen was born&nbsp;\u2013 together with her twin sister Patricia&nbsp;\u2013 on 20 July 1980 in Brazil |archivedate=29 May 2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060529012721/http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0%2C%2C2029705%2C00.html |url-status=live }}</ref> is a Brazilian model, environmental activist, author, actress, and businesswoman.\n\nSince 2001, B\u00fcndchen has been one of the highest-paid models in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/gisele-bundchen-forbes-names-richest-supermodel/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: First Billionaire Supermodel?|work=People}}</ref> In 2007, she was the 16th richest woman in the entertainment industry,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2007/01/17/richest-women-entertainment-tech-media-cz_lg_richwomen07_0118womenstars_lander.html |title=The 20 Richest Women In Entertainment |work=Forbes |date=18 January 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |first1=Lea |last1=Goldman |first2=Kiri |last2=Blakeley}}</ref> and earned the top spot on ''[[Forbes]]'' top-earning models list in 2012.<ref name=BundchenEarnings2012>{{cite news |first= Brian |last=Solomon |title=The World's Highest Paid Models |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansolomon/2012/06/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-models/|website=Forbes.com|date=14 June 2012 |accessdate=20 June 2012}}</ref> In 2014, B\u00fcndchen was listed as the 89th Most Powerful Woman in the World by ''Forbes''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eikf45ehhi/gisele-bundchen-3/|title=World's Most Powerful Women in Media and Entertainment 2014: No. 89. Gisele Bundchen|work=Forbes}}</ref>\n\n''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' has credited B\u00fcndchen with ending the [[heroin chic]] era of modeling in 1999; instead ushering in a [[Sexual attraction|sexy]], healthy look with curves and a golden tan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vogue.it/en/magazine/editor-s-blog/2014/08/august-8th|title=Gisele Bundchen - Vogue.it|access-date=2018-03-28|language=it}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was a [[Victoria's Secret#Victoria's Secret Angels|Victoria's Secret Angel]] from 2000 until mid-2007 and had signed Victoria's Secret's  biggest contract to date. She is credited with pioneering and popularizing the \"horse walk,\" a stomping movement created by a model lifting her knees high and kicking her feet to step.<ref name=\"O'Connell\">{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/public/article/SB120597258876350391.html?mod=2_1356_topbox |title=How to Walk Like a Model |last=O'Connell |first=Vanessa |date=20 March 2008 |work=The Wall Street Journal |publisher=Dow Jones & Company, Inc |accessdate=20 February 2011}}</ref> In 2007, [[Claudia Schiffer]] called B\u00fcndchen the only remaining [[supermodel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/death-of-the-supermodel|title=\"Supermodels like we once were don't exist any more\"|website=Vogue.co.uk |date=4 September 2007 |accessdate=21 October 2019|df=dmy }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen has appeared on more than 1,200 magazine covers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Style File |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/gisele-style-file |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen was nominated for Choice Movie Female Breakout Star and for Choice Movie Villain at the 2005 [[Teen Choice Awards]] for her supporting role in ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]'' (2004).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.washingtontimes.com/multimedia/collection/richest-supermodels/?page=19|title=Beauty and Bucks: Richest Supermodels|publisher=[[The Washington Times]]}}</ref> She had a supporting role in ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]'' (2006)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/movies/the-devil-wears-prada/cast/280965/|title=The Devil Wears Prada|last=|first=|date=|website=tvguide.com|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref> and was the executive producer of an educational environmental cartoon, ''Gisele & the Green Team,'' in 2010 to 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2010-dec-12-la-ig-gisele-20101212-story.html|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen talks about modeling, her family and \u2018Gisele & the Green Team\u2019|publisher=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\nIn 2016, she appeared in the Emmy award-winning documentary series Years of Living Dangerously, in the episode Fueling the Fire, sharing the episode with Arnold Schwarzenegger.<ref name=\"natgeo\">{{cite web|url=https://www.natgeotv.com/za/shows/natgeo/years-of-living-dangerously|title=Years of Living Dangerously|last=|first=|date=|website=National Geographic|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=13 December 2019}}</ref>\nB\u00fcndchen's charitable endeavors include [[Save the Children]], [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement|Red Cross]] and [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res|Doctors Without Borders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnewyork.com/blogs/threadny/Gisele-Ups-Brangelina-By-Giving-15-Million-to-the-Red-Cross-81759532.html|title=Report: Gisele Ups Brangelina By Giving $1.5 Million to the Red Cross|work=[[NBC]] New York}}</ref> She has been a [[Goodwill Ambassador]] for the [[United Nations Environment Program]] since 2009.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2009/09/21/bundchen_the_environmentalist/\n|work=Boston Globe\n|title=Bundchen the environmentalist\n|date=21 September 2009\n|first1=Mark\n|last1=Shanahan\n|first2=Meredith\n|last2=Goldstein}}</ref>\n\n==Family and early life==\nB\u00fcndchen is a [[German Brazilians|Brazilian of German descent]].<ref name=\"dw-world.de\">{{cite web | title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: \"Brazil Should Become World Champion\" | work=Carlos Albuquerque | url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,2029705,00.html | accessdate=23 January 2008}}</ref> Born to V\u00e2nia ([[n\u00e9e]] Nonnenmacher), a bank clerk pensioner, and Valdir B\u00fcndchen, a sociologist and writer, in [[Horizontina]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Southern Brazil]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.dw.com/pt-br/gisele-b\u00fcndchen-fala-sobre-futebol-e-suas-ra\u00edzes-alem\u00e3s/a-2028192 | title=Deutsche Welle: Gisele B\u00fcndchen fala sobre futebol e suas ra\u00edzes alem\u00e3s (in Portuguese) }}</ref> and raised in [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Southern Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Bennetts |first=Leslie |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/features/2009/05/gisele-bundchen200905 |title=And God Created Gisele |work=Vanity Fair |accessdate=22 November 2012}}</ref> She grew up with five sisters, Raquel, Graziela, Gabriela, Rafaela and her [[Twin#Dizygotic twins|fraternal twin]], Patr\u00edcia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/celebs-twin-siblings/ |title=Seeing Double: Celebs Who Have a Twin |publisher=People }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen learned German in school, but said she forgot the language after being out of touch with it.<ref name=\"dw-world.de\"/> In addition to Portuguese and English, B\u00fcndchen speaks Spanish and some French.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/features/gisele-b-ndchen-business-model-it-takes-more-than-just-good-looks-to-get-to-the-top-8782676.html|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Business model - it takes more than just good looks|date=23 August 2013|website=Independent.co.uk|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen aspired to be a [[volleyball]] player but joined a modeling course with her sisters Patr\u00edcia and Gabriela at their mother's insistence in 1993, in hopes to correct her bad posture.<ref name=\"WSJ\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/before-stardom-gisele-bundchen-thought-of-herself-as-strange-looking-11546445827?|title=Before Stardom, Gisele B\u00fcndchen Thought of Herself as \u2018Strange Looking\u2019|author=[[Marc Myers]]|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=3 January 2019|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> The following year, she was discovered by [[Elite Model Management]] at a shopping mall in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]].<ref name=WSJ/> B\u00fcndchen was selected for a national contest, [[Elite Model Look]] (then known as Look of the Year), in which she placed second. In early 1995, at age 14, B\u00fcndchen moved to S\u00e3o Paulo to launch her modeling career. She had her first break in 1996, at [[New York Fashion Week]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/gisele-bndchen-confirms-shes-retiring-runway/story?id=30289967|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Confirms She's Retiring From the Runway|work=ABC News|last=Rothman|first=Michael|date=April 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1997\u20132000: Career beginnings===\nB\u00fcndchen traveled to London in 1997, where she auditioned for 43 shows, but took part in only two international shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a36021/gisele-bundchen-faced-42-rejections-before-landing-first-job/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Was Rejected 42 Times Before Landing Her First Major Job|publisher=Elle}}</ref> [[Alexander McQueen]] chose her for his Spring 1998 ready-to-wear show, \"Rain!\", because of her ability to walk in towering heels on a slippery runway.<ref name=VogueJuly2018/> In 1998, B\u00fcndchen posed for [[Missoni]], [[Chlo\u00e9]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Valentino (fashion house)|Valentino]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]], [[Ralph Lauren]], and [[Versace]] campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/15/fashion/gisele-bundchen-model-supermodel.html|title=Gisele Inc.|work=New York Times|last=Trebay|first=Guy|date=May 14, 2016|access-date=October 23, 2019}}</ref> She appeared on the cover of ''[[Vogue Paris]]'', her first cover of ''British Vogue'',<ref name=NYMag/> and ''[[i-D]]'', which featured her on its cover, profiling \"A Girl Called Gisele.\"<ref name=\"vogue.com\">{{cite web |last=Sullivan |first=Robert |url=http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Gisele_Bundchen#cite_note-3 |title=Profile |website=Vogue.com |accessdate=7 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331204652/http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Gisele_Bundchen#cite_note-3 |archive-date=31 March 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 1999, B\u00fcndchen left Elite Model Management to switch to [[IMG Models]], dissatisfied with Elite's work environment.<ref name=Somethingaboutgisele>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2004/10/gisele-bundchen-fashion-film-debut|title=THERE\u2019S SOMETHING ABOUT GISELE|work=Vanity Fair|last=Andrews|first=Suzanna|date=October 2004}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to her first American ''Vogue'' cover in July 1999, dubbed \"the return of the ''sexy'' model\",<ref name=VogueJuly2018/><!--the cover stylizes it this way--> she appeared on her first group ''Vogue'' cover with fellow supermodels [[Kate Moss]], [[Amber Valletta]], [[Christy Turlington]], [[Iman (model)|Iman]], [[Lauren Hutton]], [[Naomi Campbell]], [[Stephanie Seymour]], Claudia Schiffer, [[Lisa Taylor (model)|Lisa Taylor]], [[Paulina Porizkova]], [[Carolyn Murphy]], and [[Patti Hansen]].<ref name=Gangsallhere>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/the-gangs-all-here-7-iconic-group-model-vogue-covers-photos|title=Photos: The Gang's All Here: 7 Iconic Group Model Vogue Covers|work=Vogue}}</ref> In December of that year, she once again appeared on a solo American ''Vogue'' cover.<ref name=VogueJuly2018>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-vogue-cover-july-2018-issue?verso=true|title=Can Gisele Save the Planet?|work=Vogue|last=Haskell|first=Rob|date=June 14, 2018}}</ref> She won the [[VH1]]/''Vogue'' Model of the Year for 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/gisele-bndchen-biography-2012-6|title=IN PICTURES: The Incredible Life Of Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen|work=Business Insider|last=Epstein|first=Eli|date=June 15, 2012}}</ref> Noting B\u00fcndchen was shooting five major campaigns at the age of 18, ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine editor Sally Singer said B\u00fcndchen was so successful in the industry that she deemed her an \"\u00fcber- (not super-) model.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nymag.com/nymetro/shopping/fashion/features/864/|title=Fashion Moment|work=New York Magazine|last=Singer|first=Sally|date=May 10, 1999}}</ref> She became the fourth model to appear on the cover of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine when she was named \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Most Beautiful Girl|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/hot-girl-gisele-bundchen-183901/|accessdate=October 22, 2019|work=Rolling Stone}}</ref> The same year, ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]''{{'}}s online encyclopedia of models called B\u00fcndchen the world's hottest model and said she opened a new category: the Brazilian bombshell.<ref name=\"vogue.com\"/>\n\n===2000\u20132009: Modeling breakthrough, international success, and acting debut===\nIn 2000, B\u00fcndchen appeared on 37 international ''Vogue'' covers, including three in the American edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/gisele_bundchen/covers/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Covers|work=[[Fashion Model Directory]]}}</ref> In January 2000, B\u00fcndchen was simultaneously featured on the covers of the U.S. and British editions of ''Vogue''.<ref name=BritishVogue/> The June issue co-starred [[George Clooney]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.vogue.com/issue/20000601|title=June 2000|work=Vogue Archive}}</ref> For spring 2000 fashion week, she opened shows for [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Michael Kors]], Dolce & Gabbana, [[Christian Dior]], and [[Valentino (fashion house)|Valentino]] in New York, Milan and Paris.<ref name=BritishVogue>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gisele-bundchen-biography|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Biography|work=British Vogue}}</ref> From 1998\u20132003, B\u00fcndchen was in every Dolce & Gabbana fashion campaign, totaling 11 consecutive campaigns with the brand; she returned as the face of the brand's fragrance \"The One\", in campaigns from 2006 to 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/gisele-bundchen|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen|publisher=Business of Fashion}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen retired from the runway upon signing a lucrative contract with Victoria's Secret.<ref name=Somethingaboutgisele/> In 2000, B\u00fcndchen wore Victoria's Secret's Fantasy bra, the Red Hot Fantasy Bra, worth $15 million and listed in ''Guinness World Records'' as the most expensive lingerie ever created.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/photos/25957/2018-victoria-s-secret-fashion-show-by-the-numbers/885016|title=2018 VICTORIA'S SECRET FASHION SHOW BY THE NUMBERS|work=E! Online}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen also modeled the \"Sexy Splendor Fantasy Bra\" in 2005, which was the second-most expensive bra ever made, valued at $12.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/fashion/g29045/gisele-fantasy-bra-2005/|title=Enjoy The Wonderment Of Gisele Discovering Her 2005 Fantasy Bra|work=Elle|last=Holmes|first=Sally|date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> In 2004, she appeared on another group American ''Vogue'' cover, with [[Daria Werbowy]], [[Natalia Vodianova]], [[Isabeli Fontana]], [[Karolina Kurkova]], [[Liya Kebede]], [[Hana Soukupova]], [[Gemma Ward]], and [[Karen Elson]].<ref name=Gangsallhere/> B\u00fcndchen has appeared on the covers of ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/gisele-bundchen-w-covers|title=A Tribute to Gisele B\u00fcndchen, 12-Time W Magazine Cover Star|work=W|date=July 20, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Allure (magazine)|Allure]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/gallery/gisele-bundchen-through-the-years|title=Happy Birthday, Gisele: Her Best Looks of All Time|work=Allure|date=July 20, 2015|quote=On Allure's December 2000 cover}}</ref> ''[[GQ]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/gisele-bundchen-gossip-girl|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Gossip Girl|work=GQ|date=June 1, 2008}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'', ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Time (magazine)|TIME]]'', ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'', ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'', and in the ''[[Pirelli Calendar]]''.<ref name=IMG>{{cite web|url=https://www.imgmodels.com/gisele|title=Gisele Bio|work=IMG Models}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/pirelli-calendar-photos-gisele-bundchen-cindy-crawford?verso=true|title=Exclusive: See Rare Pirelli Calendar Photos on Display at New York Fashion Week|work=Vogue}}</ref>\n\nIn acting roles, B\u00fcndchen co-starred with [[Queen Latifah]] and [[Jimmy Fallon]] in the 2004 remake of ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]'' and in 2006, B\u00fcndchen played Serena in ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen's Career Highlights |url=https://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/ |publisher=New York Mag |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was chosen by ''Time'' magazine in 2007, as one of the 100 Most Influential People in the World. In September 2007, B\u00fcndchen was photographed by [[Mario Testino]] for the cover of ''Vanity Fair''{{'}}s style issue.<ref name=NYMag>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141203055411/http://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/|archive-date=3 December 2014|url=https://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Model Profile|work=New York Magazine|access-date=22 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''Forbes'' listed her 53rd on their 2007 list of the most powerful celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |title=#53 Gisele Bundchen |url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/53/07celebrities_Gisele-Bundchen_2VPP.html |work=Forbes |date=14 June 2007 |accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> Ipanema Gisele B\u00fcndchen made an estimated [[\u00a3]]152 million (about $197 million) with more than 250 million pairs sold in 2010.<ref name=\"billionare model\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/06/02/gisele-soon-to-be-a-billionaire |title=Gisele The Billionaire |date=2 June 2011 |last=Alexander |first=Ella |accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> In May 2007, B\u00fcndchen had ended her contract with Victoria's Secret; she described this decision as closing that chapter of her career.<ref>{{cite web|last=Triggs |first=Charlotte |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20037350,00.html |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen, Victoria's Secret Part Ways |work=People |date=1 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> In August 2008, the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' listed B\u00fcndchen as the fourth most powerful person in the fashion world.<ref>{{cite web |title=Photog Remembers When Nobody Liked Gisele |url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/10/photog-remembers-when-nobody-liked-gisele/ |publisher=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132011: Continued success===\n''[[The Independent]]'' called B\u00fcndchen the biggest star in fashion history in May 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/features/gisele-bndchen-the-charmed-life-of-the-megamodel-1683088.html |work=The Independent |location=London |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Charmed life of the mega-model |date=12 May 2009 |accessdate=3 May 2010 |quote=How did the girl from Brazil become the biggest star in fashion history?}}</ref> In April 2010, B\u00fcndchen was photographed for the cover of American ''Vogue'' for the 11th time.<ref name=\"vogue.com\" /> B\u00fcndchen closed [[Balenciaga|Balenciaga']]<nowiki/>s 2010 show in a surprise appearance.<ref name=\"vogue.com\" /><ref name=\"marieclaire1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/celebrity/pictures/32510/28/rio-carnival-2011-rio-carnival-pictures-gisele-photos.html#index=9&uiSynced=true&slider=off |title=Rio Carnival pictures 2011; Gisele photos Celebrity Pictures |publisher=Marie Claire |accessdate=7 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104053222/http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/celebrity/pictures/32510/28/rio-carnival-2011-rio-carnival-pictures-gisele-photos.html#index=9&uiSynced=true&slider=off |archivedate=4 January 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She ranked third on models.com's the Money Girls list and second on the Sexiest Models list.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413124529/http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?fnumber=5&lnumber=1|archive-date=April 13, 2010|url=http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?fnumber=5&lnumber=1|title=The Money Girls are Here|website=Models.com|access-date=December 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2011, ''CEOWorld Magazine'' ranked B\u00fcndchen among their Top Accomplished Women Entertainers.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Accomplished Women Entertainers |url=http://ceoworld.biz/ceo/2011/05/18/ceoworld-richest-women-in-entertainment-world-list-accomplished-women-entertainers |newspaper=CEOWORLD magazine |date=18 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115070954/http://ceoworld.biz/ceo/2011/05/18/ceoworld-richest-women-in-entertainment-world-list-accomplished-women-entertainers |archivedate=15 January 2016 }}</ref> She was ranked No. 95 in ''[[FHM]]'' magazine's [[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women in the World 2011]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/100-sexiest-women |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111230002746/http://www.fhm.com/girls/100-sexiest-women |archive-date = 30 December 2011 | date=30 December 2011|title=FHM's 100 Sexiest Women in the World|work= FHM magazine}}</ref> In 2007, B\u00fcndchen was named the World's Richest Supermodel.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20047102,00.html | title = Gisele Bundchen Named World's Richest Model | work = [[People (magazine)|People]] | accessdate =1 September 2011 }}</ref> On April 11, 2008, a black-and-white photo of B\u00fcndchen that was shot by [[Irving Penn]] was auctioned for $193,000. The picture was one of dozens from the collection of Gert Elfering that were sold at [[Christie's]] International in New York. B\u00fcndchen's picture brought the highest price.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2008/04/12/photo_of_gisele_brings_big_bucks/?p1=Well_MostPop_Emailed7 |title=Photo of Gisele brings big bucks|work=Boston Globe |date=12 April 2008 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |first1=Carol |last1=Beggy |first2=Mark |last2=Shanahan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclusivo.terra.com.br/interna/0,,OI2738910-EI1118,00.html |title=\"Foto de Gisele nua \u00e9 comprada em leil\u00e3o por US$193 mile\", (Portuguese) xclusivo.terra.com.br|publisher=Exclusivo.terra.com.br |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref>\n\nBy 2010, B\u00fcndchen had appeared on two ''Vogue Shape'' issue covers, more than any other celebrity or model.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/the-past-decade-of-shape-issues/#1 |title=Shaping a Decade: Ten Years of Vogue Shape Issue |accessdate=14 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130419050947/http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/the-past-decade-of-shape-issues/#1 |archivedate=19 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She ranked No. 45 in the 2011 FHM Australia list of 100 Sexiest Women in the World.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com.au/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2011-gallery.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513014056/http://www.fhm.com.au/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2011-gallery.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 May 2011 |title=FHM's 100 Sexiest Women in the World 2011 |accessdate=1 September 2011 }}</ref> In 2011, ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]'' named B\u00fcndchen as No. 25 of the 100 Hottest Women of All Time.<ref>{{cite web|title=The 100 Hottest Women of All-Time|url=http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-all-time|work=[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|accessdate=3 January 2012|year=2011}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen closed the 2011 Givenchy spring-summer fashion show in a surprise appearance during Paris Fashion Week.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2011/10/gisele_bundchen_closes_out_giv.html |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Closes Out Givenchy's All-Star Show&nbsp;\u2013 The Cut |publisher=Nymag.com |date=27 December 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2013}}</ref> That year, B\u00fcndchen launched eco-friendly Sejaa Pure Skincare, a [[Cosmetics|skin care]] [[Product lining|product line]] using all-natural ingredients.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/style/gisele-bundchen-to-launch-eco-friendly-skincare-line/|title=Gisele Bundchen to Launch Eco-Friendly Skincare Line|work=People|date=2010-03-14}}</ref>\n\nShe appeared on eight ''Vogue'' covers in 2011, more than any other model or celebrity that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fashionista.com/2011/12/this-year-in-vogue-the-covers/ |title=This Year in Vogue: An Analysis of all the Covers from 2011&nbsp;\u2013 Fashionista: Fashion Industry News, Designers, Runway Shows, Style Advice |publisher=Fashionista.com |date=8 December 2011 |accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> Her July ''Vogue Brasil'' 2011 cover that was shot in the [[Amazon Rainforest|Amazon]] sold 70,743 copies, making it the magazine's highest-selling issue.<ref>[http://vogue.globo.com/mundo-vogue/a-vogue-brasileira-mais-vendida-de-todos-os-tempos/ \"A Vogue brasileira mais vendida de todos os tempos\"] 10 February 2012, Brazil Vogue (in Portuguese) {{webarchive |url=https://archive.today/20120718095012/http://vogue.globo.com/mundo-vogue/a-vogue-brasileira-mais-vendida-de-todos-os-tempos/ |date=18 July 2012 }}</ref> In early 2011, Procter & Gamble's [[Pantene]] shampoo sales increased 40 percent in Latin America after B\u00fcndchen started representing the product.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2011/05/05/top-earning-models.html|title=The World's Top-Earning Models | work=Forbes | first1=Keren|last1=Blankfeld|first2=Steven|last2=Bertoni|date=5 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u2013present: Modeling campaigns and music endeavors===\nIn spring 2012, B\u00fcndchen was featured in three spring campaigns, Versace, Givenchy, and Salvatore Ferragamo.<ref>[http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/2011/12/22/the-year-of-gisele-and-lisbeth/ \"The Year of Gisele and Lisbeth?\"] 22 December 2011, Elle {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504023508/http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/2011/12/22/the-year-of-gisele-and-lisbeth/ |date=4 May 2012 }}</ref> She became the face of Banco do Brasil's first global ad campaign in 2012.<ref>[http://www.giselebundchen.com/novidades/10084/from-brazil-to-the-world \"From Brazil to the World\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301034736/http://www.giselebundchen.com/novidades/10084/from-brazil-to-the-world |date=1 March 2012 }} News, 27 February 2012, Gisele web site</ref>\nIn April 2012, ''Time'' listed B\u00fcndchen on its All-TIME 100 Fashion Icons list, which highlighted the most influential fashion icons since 1923.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2110513_2110628,00.html |title=All-TIME 100 Fashion Icons&nbsp;\u2013 Gisele B\u00fcndchen |author=Katy Steinmetz |date=2 April 2012 |work=Time |accessdate=2 April 2012}}</ref> ''Vogue'' included B\u00fcndchen in its spotlight of the 10 women who had most appeared on its covers to honor the magazine's 120th anniversary in August 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/fashions-familiar-faces-the-women-who-have-most-often-graced-the-cover-of-vogue/#1|title=Fashion's Familiar Faces: The Women Who Have Most Often Graced the Cover of Vogue|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=19 December 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121219140203/http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/fashions-familiar-faces-the-women-who-have-most-often-graced-the-cover-of-vogue/#1|archivedate=19 December 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:FIFA World Cup 2014 Final - Gisele B\u00fcndchen.jpg|thumb|right|268x268px|B\u00fcndchen in 2014]]\nB\u00fcndchen made 5,600 appearances in commercials in Brazil in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/QUEM-News/noticia/2012/12/camila-pitanga-supera-gianecchini-e-neymar-em-campanhas-publicitarias.html|title=Camila Pitanga supera Gianecchini e Neymar em campanhas publicit\u00e1rias &#124; Quem - Not\u00edcias em QUEM News |publisher=Revistaquem.globo.com |date=27 December 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2013}}</ref> She replaced Kate Moss as the face of [[David Yurman]] in August 2012. She was photographed by [[Peter Lindbergh]] for the fall 2012 campaign.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/26/kate-moss-david-yurman-gisele-bundchen-2012_n_1831200.html |title=Kate Moss Reportedly Replaced By Gisele Bundchen As The Face Of David Yurman |publisher=The Huffington Post |date=26 August 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2013 |first=Rebecca |last=Adams}}</ref> By 2012, B\u00fcndchen had appeared on 120 ''Vogue'' covers. She holds the record for appearing on the most ''Vogue Brasil'' covers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/125434-gisele-bundchen-covers-vogue-brazil-for-what-seems-like-the-millionth-time-photo|title=Gisele Bundchen Covers 'Vogue' Brazil For What Seems Like The Millionth Time \u2014 PHOTO|work=Bustle}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2013, B\u00fcndchen became the face of Chanel's make-up line, Les Beiges. The campaign was photographed by Mario Testino.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fashiongonerogue.com/gisele-bundchen-lands-first-chanel-campaign-with-les-beiges-collection/ |title=GISELE BUNDCHEN LANDS FIRST CHANEL CAMPAIGN WITH \"LES BEIGES\" COLLECTION |publisher=FashionGoneRogue |date=4 February 2013 |accessdate=4 February 2013}}</ref> For Louis Vuitton's spring/summer 2014 campaign, Marc Jacobs chose B\u00fcndchen, [[Catherine Deneuve]], [[Sofia Coppola]], [[Fan Bingbing]], Caroline de Maigret and [[Edie Campbell]] as his muses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wwd.com/media-news/fashion-memopad/portrait-of-a-lady-7319938|title=Louis Vuitton Campaign a Tribute to Marc Jacobs' Muses|date=19 December 2013}}</ref> In December 2013, B\u00fcndchen became [[Pantene]]'s ambassador, a deal worth $4 million per year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20131227005266/en/Gisele-B%C3%BCndchen-Sizzles-Pantene%E2%80%99s-Newest-Ambassador#.Ur4176go7GV|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Sizzles as Pantene's Newest Ambassador|website=Businesswire.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://glamurama.uol.com.br/mais-um-contrato-mundial-para-gisele-bundchen-engordar-o-cofrinho/|title=Mais um contrato mundial para Gisele B\u00fcndchen engordar o cofrinho ...|website=Glamurama.uol.com.br}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen - Rio 2016 cropped (square).jpg|thumb|228x228px|B\u00fcndchen at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]]|alt=|left]]B\u00fcndchen released a cover of [[the Kinks]] \"[[All Day and All of the Night]]\" as a contribution to H&M's 2013 charity campaign.<ref name=\"H&M\" /> She contributed to H&M's 2014 charity campaign by teaming with [[French people|French]] music producer and DJ [[Bob Sinclar]] to record a cover of [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]]'s 1979 classic \"[[Heart of Glass (song)|Heart of Glass]]\", on which she was credited as Gisele.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://video.repubblica.it/spettacoli-e-cultura/gisele-regina-dance-per-bob-sinclar-canta-in-bikini-animalier/163445/161935 |title= Gisele, regina dance per Bob Sinclar: canta in bikini animalier |publisher= [[Repubblica Radio TV|Repubblica TV]] |date= 22 April 2014\n|accessdate= 12 July 2014|language=it}}</ref> The single charted in France, Germany, Spain, Austria and Belgium.<ref name=\"H&M\">{{cite news|first= Olivia |last= Bergin |title= Gisele Bundchen to release charity single for H&M campaign |url= http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10282629/Gisele-Bundchen-to-release-charity-single-for-HandM-campaign.html |newspaper= [[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date= 3 September 2013 |accessdate= 12 July 2014 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, B\u00fcndchen was chosen as the spokeswoman for [[Chanel No. 5]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/baz-and-gisele-take-five-7692136|title=Baz Luhrmann and Gisele B\u00fcndchen Take Five|website=Wwd.com}}</ref> Within the first quarter of 2014, B\u00fcndchen appeared on 17 international editions of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]],'' including the Brazilian, German, Italian, Canadian, Japanese and Chinese editions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10922406/Gis-Elle-Bundchens-17-cover-marathon.html |title=Gis-Elle Bundchen's 17 cover marathon |author=Olivia Lidbury |website=telegraph.co.uk |accessdate=30 August 2015 |date=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627023228/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10922406/Gis-Elle-Bundchens-17-cover-marathon.html |archivedate=27 June 2014 }}</ref> Under Armour signed B\u00fcndchen to a multiyear deal in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-09-02/under-armour-signs-model-gisele-bundchen-in-push-to-entice-women.html|title=Under Armour Signs Model Gisele in Push to Entice Women|author=Matt Townsend|work=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=29 March 2015|date=2 September 2014}}</ref> In 2014 and 2015, B\u00fcndchen appeared in more television commercial spots than any other Brazilian celebrity in the course of one year in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen lidera ranking de famosos em comerciais de TV|url=http://g1.globo.com/economia/midia-e-marketing/noticia/2016/01/gisele-bundchen-lidera-ranking-de-famosos-em-comerciais-de-tv.html|website=G1.globo.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/economia/midia-e-marketing/noticia/2014/12/gisele-bundchen-desbanca-neymar-em-ranking-de-aparicao-em-comercial.html|title=G1 - Gisele B\u00fcndchen desbanca Neymar em ranking de apari\u00e7\u00e3o em comercial|work=Midia e Marketing|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele getting ready for the Met Gala (Nino Munoz).jpg|thumb|upright|B\u00fcndchen getting ready for the Met Gala, 2017]]\n\nB\u00fcndchen was featured in the 2015 Guinness World Record book as the model who earned the most money from June 2014 to June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele no Guiness &#91;sic&#93; Book como modelo mais bem paga do mundo|url=http://glamurama.uol.com.br/gisele-no-guiness-book-como-modelo-mais-bem-paga-do-mundo/|website=Glamura.uol.com.br|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\nB\u00fcndchen's $700 Taschen book released in celebration of her 20th year career sold out in one day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele's $700 Book Sells Out|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2015/11/09/gisele-bundchen-taschen-book-700-sold-out|website=Vogue.co.uk|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\nBy 2015, B\u00fcndchen appeared in more than 550 ad campaigns, 2000 magazine covers, 3500 magazine editorials and 800 fashion shows.<ref>{{cite web|title=Runways - Gisele B\u00fcndchen|url=http://giselebundchen.com/highlights/desfiles/|website=Giselebundchen.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen appeared at the [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium]] at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2016 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] on August 5, 2016.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/05/gisele-bundchen-olympics-opening-ceremony-rio | title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen dazzles at the Olympics Opening Ceremony in Rio | first=Breanne L. | last=Heldman | work=Entertainment Weekly | accessdate=5 August 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/models/news/a16703/gisele-bundchen-rio-olympics-2016/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen to Walk the 2016 Olympics Opening Ceremony|date=18 July 2016|website=Harpersbazaar.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen 2006.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|right|B\u00fcndchen in 2006]]\n\n''Forbes'' ranked B\u00fcndchen No. 61 on its Most Powerful Celebrities list in 2012.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/05/16/jennifer-lopez-tops-celebrity-100-list/ \"J.Lo's Stunning Career Reincarnation Puts Her No. 1 On The Celebrity 100\"] 16 May 2012, Forbes.</ref>\n''Forbes'' ranked her fourth on the World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrity list in May 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson Antunes |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/2/ |title=The Worlds Most Powerful Latino Celebrities |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> In 2013, she ranked No. 5 on the ''Forbes'' 10 Most Powerful Businesswomen in Brazil''.''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eifl45ekgd/no-5-gisele-bundchen/|title=The 10 Most Powerful Businesswomen In Brazil|accessdate=5 June 2013 | work=Forbes|first=Anderson|last=Antunes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, B\u00fcndchen's Ipanema sandals sold about 25 million pairs annually and accounted for more than 60 percent of shoe manufacturer [[Grendene]]'s annual exports of about $250 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2014/01/10/brazils-newest-billionaire-has-gisele-to-thank-as-he-joins-forbes-list-of-the-worlds-richest//|title=Brazils newest billionaire has Giselle to thank as he joins Forbes list of the worlds richest|website=Forbes.com |accessdate=15 February 2014 | first=Anderson|last=Antunes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, B\u00fcndchen signed a contract with [[Under Armour]], which is reportedly on par with the endorsement compensations of professional athletes and exceeds her former [[Victoria's Secret]] contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2014/09/03/gisele-bundchens-new-under-armour-gig-is-the-supermodels-most-profitable-yet/#70c52b134174|title=UPDATED: Gisele Bundchen's New Under Armour Gig|last=Altunes|first=Anderson|work=Forbes}}</ref> In 2016, Under Armour's CEO Kevin Plank said sales for the company's women's brand had increased because of its association with B\u00fcndchen.<ref>{{cite news|title=Under Armour is using Gisele for an aggressive expansion plan \u2014 and it should terrify Lululemon|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/under-armour-womens-business-could-beat-lululemon-2016-1|website=Businessinsider.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Gisele released her book called ''Lessons: My Path to a Meaningful Life'', which was a [[New York Times]] bestseller and was the best selling book for over six months in the non-fiction category in Brazil.<ref name = usatoday3>{{cite web | url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2018/10/02/gisele-bundchen-book-lessons-tom-brady-breast-implants-kids/1482259002/ \n| publisher = USA Today | title = From breast implants to life with Tom Brady: 5 'Lessons' from Gisele Bundchen's book| accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref><ref name = voguebook>{{cite web | url = https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-lessons-book-interview | publisher = Vogue | title = \"I Never Go a Day Without Dessert\"\u2014This and More, From Gisele B\u00fcndchen\u2019s New Book, Lessons | accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref><ref name = boston>{{cite web | url = https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2018/10/14/gisele-lessons-becomes-bestseller/MKYTB2ehYnzeYMCeyEax2N/story.html | publisher = Boston.com | title = Gisele\u2019s \u2018Lessons\u2019 becomes a bestseller| accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref> The proceeds from her book went to support social and environmental causes.<ref name = boston/>\n\n==Public image==\nIn September 2000, ''[[Newsweek]]'' reported on a survey conducted by Brazilian magazine Capricho, where 86 percent of Brazilian teenagers said they wanted to become fashion models. Capricho attributed the interest in modeling to B\u00fcndchen.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Year's Model|url=http://www.newsweek.com/years-model-159397|website=Newsweek.com|accessdate=1 November 2014|date=25 September 2000}}</ref>\n\nBy 2014, B\u00fcndchen was listed by ''Forbes'' as the 89th most powerful woman in the world.<ref name=Forbes14>{{cite news|title=The World's 100 Most Powerful Women|url=https://www.forbes.com/power-women/list/2/#tab:overall|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=26 June 2014}}</ref>\nForbes Brasil listed B\u00fcndchen as the No. 2 biggest Brazilian celebrity of 2015 based on media presence and influence in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Year's Model|url=https://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320015943/http://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1|archivedate=20 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn a 2006 ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' survey, more than 50 percent of American stylists asked gave B\u00fcndchen the title of the best hair in Hollywood.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele Bundchen&nbsp;\u2013 Gisele Tops Elle Hair Poll|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/gisele%20tops%20elle%20hair%20poll_1004086  |publisher=Contactmusic.com |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> A February 2008 survey of more than 20,000 plastic surgeons in 84 countries revealed B\u00fcndchen was the celebrity most mentioned for patients having work done on their abdomens and hair, and the second-most mentioned celebrity in the breasts category.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.science20.com/newswire/celebrity_influences_on_plastic_surgery |title=Celebrity Influences on Plastic Surgery |accessdate=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen was second on ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''{{'}}s World's Most Beautiful poll in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/online/daily/2009/04/angelina-jolie-is-the-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-world |title=Angelina Jolie Is the Most Beautiful Woman in the World|accessdate=27 December 2012}}</ref>\nIn January 2011, B\u00fcndchen's was the most desired female body on the ''14th Annual Famed Hottest Looks'' survey.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2011/01/06/gisele-bundchen-mark-wahlberg-plastic-surgery-celeb-bodies/ |publisher=Fox News |title=EXCLUSIVE: 14th Annual America's Most Wanted Celebrity Body Parts |date=6 January 2011}}</ref> In 2011, B\u00fcndchen was one of three women to make [[AskMen.com]]\u2019s annual \"Most Desirable Women\" list every year for 10 consecutive years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2011/02/01/askmen-99-most-desirable-women-blake-lively-mila-kunis-sofia-vergara-angelina-jolie-gisele-beyonc/ |title=Who's the Most Desirable Actress in Hollywood? |publisher=Imnotobsessed.com |date=19 September 2011 |accessdate=24 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130126113338/http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2011/02/01/askmen-99-most-desirable-women-blake-lively-mila-kunis-sofia-vergara-angelina-jolie-gisele-beyonc/ |archivedate=26 January 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen is ranked No. 4 on ''Forbes Brasil''{{'}}s list of the 100 most influential Brazilian celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|title=FORBES Brasil traz as 100 celebridades mais influentes do pa\u00eds em 2013|url=http://forbesbrasil.br.msn.com/blog/post-redacao.aspx?post=daaec777-6984-41d0-b444-2f2d194d4ed5#scpshrtu|website=Forbesbrasil.br.msn.com|accessdate=20 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320173646/http://forbesbrasil.br.msn.com/blog/post-redacao.aspx?post=daaec777-6984-41d0-b444-2f2d194d4ed5#scpshrtu|archive-date=20 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\nIn May 2014, B\u00fcndchen was ranked No. 89 on ''Forbes''{{'}} 100 Most Powerful Women in the world, the only model on the list.<ref>{{cite web|title=The World's Most Powerful Women 2014 - Forbes|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carolinehoward/2014/05/28/the-worlds-most-powerful-women-2014/|website=Forbes.com}}</ref>\nIn November 2014, ''Forbes Brasil'' ranked B\u00fcndchen fifth of the 25 biggest celebrities in Brazil, moving her up to second in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=25 maiores celebridades do Brasil em 2014 - Forbes Brasil |url=http://www.forbesbrasil.co/listas/15-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2014/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204193653/http://www.forbesbrasil.co/listas/15-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2014/ |archivedate=4 December 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"fashionweekdaily.com\">{{cite web|title=Stuart Weitzman's Susan Duffy, The Image Innovator - Daily Front Row|url=http://fashionweekdaily.com/stuart-weitzmans-susan-duffy-image-innovator/|website=Fashionweekdaily.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=RANKING: 25 maiores celebridades do Brasil em 2015 - Forbes Brasil|url=https://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320015943/http://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1/|archivedate=20 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVogue Italia called B\u00fcndchen the \"King Midas of fashion\" in February 2012, saying companies that invest in her reap the awards of her representation.<ref>{{cite web|author=vogue.it |url=http://www.vogue.it/en/people-are-talking-about/obsession-of-the-day/2012/02/gisele-bundchen-forbes |title=Gisele the Millionaire |publisher=Vogue.it |date=22 November 2011 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> An Esprit public awareness campaign featuring B\u00fcndchen helped raise consumer awareness 9 percent in Germany and 19 percent in China.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120321163229/http://svesty.com/index.php/fashion-news/113-gisele-bundchen-for-the-esprit-spring-summer-2012-collection 'Gisele Bundchen For The Esprit Spring Summer 2012 Collection\"] 15 March 2012, Svesty Fashion</ref>\n\nIn 2016 B\u00fcndchen participated in \u201cThe Beginning of Life\u201d [[documentary]] showing that the early years are the ones that structure the life of a person and that one of the biggest advances in [[neuroscience]] is the discovery that babies are much more than a [[genetic load]].<ref name = unicef>{{cite web | url = https://www.unicef.org/media/media_91198.html | publisher = UNICEF | title =Pioneering new film \"The Beginning of Life\" to be released across global streaming and multimedia platforms | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nSince the 2000s, B\u00fcndchen's main focus has been social and [[Human impact on the environment|environmental causes]].<ref name = nytimes/><ref name = vanity/> She has also supported the [[Breast Cancer Campaign]] to educate women on how to perform a [[Breast self-examination|breast self-exam]].<ref name = metro>{{cite web | url = https://metro.co.uk/2018/03/18/tom-brady-opens-mothers-battle-breast-cancer-really-well-7397533/ | publisher = Metro | title = Tom Brady opens up about mother\u2019s battle with breast cancer: \u2018She\u2019s doing really well\u2019| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charitable activities===\n[[File:Gisele Bundchen with the United Nations 2010.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|right|B\u00fcndchen traveling with the United Nations in 2010]]\n\nB\u00fcndchen donated $150,000 to Brazil's [[Fome Zero|Zero Hunger program]].<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/30/world/brazil-s-war-on-hunger-off-to-a-slow-start.html |title=Brazil's War on Hunger Off to a Slow Start|work=New York Times |date=30 March 2003 |accessdate=21 October 2019 |first=Larry |last=Rohter}}</ref> She designed a limited necklace edition for ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', crafted by jewelers Gumuchian Fils, which were sold to raise money for [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/fashion/fashion-news/news/g22264/how-gisele-spends-it/?slide=6 |title=How Gisele Spends It |work=Harpers Bazaar |date=15 July 2014 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAn iPod autographed by B\u00fcndchen and loaded with her personal playlist was auctioned, and proceeds were donated to [[Music Rising]], a campaign founded in 2005, to replace lost or destroyed instruments of musicians in the Gulf Coast Region after [[Hurricane Katrina|hurricane disasters]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/gisele-bundchen/news |title=Page 1 of 1 for Gisele Bundchen Charity News |publisher=Looktothestars.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen became the face of [[American Express]]'s [[Product Red]]-affiliated card in 2006.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2946069/Gisele-Bundchen-signed-up-to-boost-Amex-Red-card.html|title=Gisele Bundchen signed up to boost Amex 'Red' card|publisher=The Telegraph|date=24 August 2006}}</ref> A portion of earnings from the credit card are donated to HIV/AIDS victims in Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/lifestyle/2006-09/01/content_679601.htm |title=China Daily&nbsp;\u2013 Lifestyle |work=China Daily |date=1 September 2006 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> In the same year she took part in the [[Keep a Child Alive|I am African]] fundraising campaign to make [[AIDS treatment]] accessible to all of [[Africa]].<ref name = borgen>{{cite web | url = https://www.borgenmagazine.com/gisele-bundchens-philanthropy/|publisher = Borgen magazine | title =  Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen is Super-Charitable| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref> In 2009, she appeared on 30 covers of the international issues of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' wearing Product Red clothing and posing with products from companies that support its mission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.exposay.com/v/26819/gisele-bundchen-latest-promoter-product-red-clothing/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen To Be Latest Promoter Of (Product) Red Clothing & Products |publisher=Fashion.exposay.com |date=12 May 2011 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903212927/http://fashion.exposay.com/v/26819/gisele-bundchen-latest-promoter-product-red-clothing/ |archivedate=3 September 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joinred.com/News/Articles/ArticleDetail/09-01-15/Elle_Magazine_Features_Gisele_for_RED.aspx |archive-url=https://archive.today/20090228195424/http://www.joinred.com/News/Articles/ArticleDetail/09-01-15/Elle_Magazine_Features_Gisele_for_RED.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=28 February 2009 |title=Elle Magazine Features Gisele for (RED) |publisher=Joinred.com |date=22 July 2009 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen started The Luz Foundation in 2007, a project to empower girls and help them deal with self-esteem issues.<ref name = vanity>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2009/05/gisele-bundchen200905 |title=\u2026 And God Created Gisele|publisher=Vanity Fair |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, B\u00fcndchen auctioned a collection of diamonds to benefit the Diamond Empowerment Fund, a nonprofit organization to education initiatives in countries where diamonds are a natural resource. The collection featured the Ponahalo Diamonds which were valued at $2 million to $4 million, a 6-carat diamond ring worth $120,000-$150,000 and a 3.35-carat Sabbadini diamond ring worth $15,000-$20,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/giseles-sale-running-bases-yes-we-khan-1784084/#/article/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/giseles-sale-running-bases-yes-we-khan-1784084?full=true|title=Gisele\u2019s Sale\u2026 Running Bases\u2026 Yes, We Khan\u2026|last=WWD staff|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Women's Wear Daily|publication-date=17 September 2008|accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\nIn 2010, she donated $1.5 million to the [[Red Cross]] to aid the relief effort in [[Haiti]] after seeing the devastation done by the earthquake.<ref>{{cite news|last=Meredith Goldstein|first=Mark Shanahan|title=Gisele gives $1.5m to Haiti relief effort|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2010/01/15/gisele_gives_15m_to_haiti_relief_effort/|accessdate=20 December 2012|newspaper=The Boston Globe|date=15 January 2010}}</ref> The donation put B\u00fcndchen tied for 14th on The Giving Back Fund's list of 30 celebrities who made the largest donations to charity in 2011.<ref>[http://www.givingback.org/Programs_Services/GivingBack30_2011.html 2011 Giving Back 30 Released in Parade Magazine & Parade.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215132647/http://www.givingback.org/Programs_Services/GivingBack30_2011.html |date=15 February 2012 }} Giving Back.org</ref>\n\nIn 2010, together with former president [[Bill Clinton]], B\u00fcndchen joined the event that partnered [[Pantene]] and the Children's Safe Drinking Water Program to provide [[clean water]] to people in need.<ref name=\"cnnnews\">{{cite web|url=https://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/prnewswire/MM69324.htm|title=Pantene Pro-V Announces Launch of 'Healthy Hair for Healthy Water,' First-Ever Pantene Global Cause Program|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=CNN Money|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=28 December 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen and Indonesian singer-songwriter [[Anggun]] announced the kick-off of the Healthy Hair for Healthy Water program at [[Procter & Gamble|P&G]]'s reception that was held in conjunction with the 2010 [[Clinton Global Initiative]] in [[New York City]]. B\u00fcndchen also attended the Brazil Foundation's 8th Annual Gala to raise funds for fighting challenges faced by poor communities in [[Brazil]].<ref name = womenswear>{{cite web | url = https://wwd.com/eye/parties/the-brazil-foundation-heats-up-the-met-3300519/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | title = The Brazil Foundation Heats Up The Met| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen created an exclusive design for [[SIGG]] water bottles, with proceeds going to [[WaterAid|WaterCan NGO]], a humanitarian organization in [[Canada]] that provides the poorest people in the world access to [[clean water]], [[toilets]], and information on [[hygiene]].<ref name = vogueindia>{{cite web | url = https://www.vogue.in/content/5-reasons-why-you-should-care-about-eco-fashion-week | publisher = Vogue India | title = 5 reasons why you should care about Eco Fashion Week| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Environmental work===\nIn 2004, after visiting an [[Indian tribe]] at the [[Xingu peoples|Xingu]] region in [[Brazil]] and seeing firsthand the problems those communities were facing due to [[water pollution]] and [[deforestation]] B\u00fcndchen decided she had to do something to help bring attention to social and environmental issues. She advocated for the cause and through the years she has supported different projects, especially forest and water related projects in the [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon]] and [[Atlantic Rainforest]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bundchen |first1=Gisele |title=Bio by Patricia Bundchen, Gisele's twin sister. |url=http://giselebundchen.com/bio/ |website=Gisele Bundchen |publisher=Gisele Bundchen |accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, she signed a \"Hotter than I Should Be\u201d T-shirt that was auctioned on [[eBay]] for the [[World Wide Fund for Nature|World Wildlife Fund]] to support the charity's campaign to raise awareness about the causes and impacts of climate change.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worldwildlife.org/press-releases/celebrities-say-they-re-hotter-than-they-should-be|title=Celebrities Say They're 'Hotter than They Should Be'|last=|first=|date=October 3, 2007|website=WWF|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen returned to her hometown of [[Horizontina]] in 2008 and with her family launched Projeto \u00c1gua Limpa (Clean Water Project), which implements sustainable environmental management and promotes the recovery of [[riparian]] vegetation and the micro basins of the [[region]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|title=United Nations Environment Programme|website=United Nations Environment Programme environment for development|publisher=United Nations|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111223155449/http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|archivedate=December 23, 2011|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> More than one million trees were planted in B\u00fcndchen's name following her 2008 American Photo cover to promote Forests of the Future, a project to assist in the reforestation of the Brazilian [[Atlantic Forest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/1453-gisele-bundchen-goes-au-naturel-for-rainforests |title=Gisele Bundchen Goes Au Naturel For Rainforests |publisher=Looktothestars.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2009, B\u00fcndchen co-hosted the [[Rainforest Alliance]]'s annual gala to honor leaders in sustainability.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|title=UNEP Goodwill Ambassadors|date=23 December 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111223155449/http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|archive-date=23 December 2011|accessdate=8 April 2019}}</ref> In May 2011, B\u00fcndchen was named Harvard's 2011 [[Global Environmental Citizen Award|Global Environmental Citizen]] in recognition of her eco-efforts.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zalopany |first=Chelsea |url=http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Eco_Fashion |title=Eco Fashion&nbsp;\u2013 Voguepedia |publisher=Vogue.com |accessdate=7 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121223174633/http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Eco_Fashion |archivedate=23 December 2012 }}</ref> In November 2011, she was awarded Greenest Celebrity at the 2011 International Green awards at the National History Museum of London.<ref>{{cite web|author=Angie Tarantino |url=http://www.theenvironmentalblog.org/2011/12/super-model-gisele-bundchen-greenest-celebrity-award/ |title=Super model Gisele Bundchen wins greenest celebrity award |publisher=Theenvironmentalblog.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512223332/http://www.theenvironmentalblog.org/2011/12/super-model-gisele-bundchen-greenest-celebrity-award/ |archivedate=12 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen donates proceeds from the sales from her [[Ipanema]] sandals to a different charity each year. Starting in 2006, B\u00fcndchen dedicated a percentage of the sales of her line of sandals to environmental projects including \u201cY Ikatu Xingu\u201d, meaning \"Save the Good Water of Xingu\", the project aimed to recover and protect springs and headwaters of the [[Xingu River]] in Brazil. In 2007 she supported [[World Wildlife Fund]] project \u201cNascentes do Brasil\u201d and \u201cDe olho nos manaciais\u201d from ISA. In 2008, the project supported was \u201cFlorestas do futuro\" from SOS Mata Atlantica, a [[reforestation]] program for recovery of [[native species]], which contributes to water conservation and [[biodiversity]]. A forest was named after her, the Gisele B\u00fcndchen Forest, where more than 25000 seedlings of 100 different tree species where planted in her honor, which recovered more than 15 [[hectares]] of Atlantic Forest. In 2011, the donation went to the Socio-Environmental Institute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gisele-bundchen-biography|title=Gisele Bundchen|last=Milligan|first=Lauren|date=November 28, 2011|website=Vogue|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> In 2009, she also helped the \"Tamar Project\", a research [[initiative]] and [[environmental protection]] of the five [[species]] of [[sea turtles]] along the Brazilian coast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a18542/gisele-bundchen-looking-longingly-at-things/|title= Gisele B\u00fcndchen Looks Longingly At Baby Turtles And Other Things |work=Elle|access-date=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, B\u00fcndchen planted a sapling of [[Lecythis pisonis|Sapucaia]] tree during her visit to Green Nation Fest, an event that occurs every year during the Environment Week and, that year, prior to the realization of Rio +20.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://m.diariolibre.com/actualidad/gisele-bndchen-planta-un-rbol-para-promover-da-mundial-del-medio-ambiente-IIDL338891 | title= Gisele B\u00fcndchen planta un \u00e1rbol para promover D\u00eda Mundial del Medio Ambiente | publisher = Diario Libre | accessdate = 3 April 2020}}</ref> Over the years B\u00fcndchen participated in several [[United Nations]] campaigns to fight against climate change. She participated in challenges on [[World Environment Day]] to mobilize people to take action in helping protect the forest, the wildlife, the green economy and to encourage people to reduce their [[food waste]].<ref name = globe>{{cite web | url = https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2019/09/05/the-amazon-rainforest-still-fire-and-gisele-bundchen-speaking-out-about/uxMuHo0bJbDZv7ucLWBMVK/story.html | publisher = The Boston Globe | title = The Amazon rainforest is still on fire, and Gisele Bundchen is speaking out about it| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen attended Champions of the Earth and Equator Prize ceremonies multiples times.<ref name = popsug>{{cite web | url = https://www.popsugar.com/celebrity/photo-gallery/31926620/image/31942074/Gisele-B%C3%BCndchen-attended-Champions-Earth-UN-event | publisher = PopSugar | accessdate = 2 January 2020 | title =  Basketball Stars, Bikini Babes, and More of the Week's Cute Celebrity Candids}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, B\u00fcndchen supported the [[United Nations]] campaign against food waste, [[World Environment Day#2013|THINK.EAT.SAVE.]] B\u00fcndchen and chef [[Eric Ripert]] participated in the [[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today Show]] program where they showed that it is possible to cook more efficiently.<ref name = usatoday>{{cite web | url = https://www.today.com/food/dont-waste-it-3-ways-use-roast-chicken-leftovers-4B11198371 | publisher = Today Show | title = Don't waste it! 3 ways to use roast chicken leftovers| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen and her husband promote the [[Earth Hour]] global movement, a symbolic act promoted worldwide by the [[World Wildlife Foundation]] in which governments, [[companies]], and people demonstrate concern for the environment, turning off their lights for sixty [[minutes]].<ref name = grist>{{cite web | url = https://grist.org/article/2010-03-24-celeb-couple-awkwardly-ask-you-to-dim-lights-earth-hour/ |publisher = The Grist | title =Celeb couple awkwardly asks you to dim the lights for Earth Hour | accessdate = 1 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, B\u00fcndchen joined the Rainforest Alliance [[board of directors]].<ref name = rainforest>{{cite web | url = https://www.rainforest-alliance.org/press-releases/gisele-bundchen-board-member | publisher = Rainforest Alliance | title = Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins Rainforest Alliance Board of Directors| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> Later that year she attended, as a guest of honor the spring annual gala, a ceremony that recognized the industry champions that have sustainability as a priority. In 2014 B\u00fcndchen supported the SOKO + [[EGM: prevention of violence against women and girls|The United Nations Trust Fund to End Violence Against Women]] partnership to support the financial and physical security of women and girls around the world.<ref name = amsterdam>{{cite web | url = http://amsterdamftv.com/archives/32160 | title = Model Gisele B\u00fcndchen supports the project that helps eradicating violence against women and girls| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> SOKO artisans in Kenya created a pair of handmade bracelets to raise awareness for the fund. B\u00fcndchen had her work in the defense of the environment recognized and was appointed as Goodwill Ambassador for the [[United Nations Environment Programme]] (UNEP).<ref name = parade/> Since then, B\u00fcndchen has helped UNEP in the mission of raising awareness and inspiring action to protect the environment.<ref name = parade>{{cite web | url = https://parade.com/96477/parade/gisele-bundchen-goodwill-ambassador/ | publisher = Parade | title =  Gisele Bundchen Named Goodwill Ambassador | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, she joined the climate change documentary show [[Years of Living Dangerously]] as one of its celebrity correspondents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boston.com/culture/celebs/2016/06/02/gisele-shows-us-shes-earth-goddess-busy-saving-planet |title=Gisele will appear on National Geographic's 'Years of Living Dangerously' |publisher=boston.com |accessdate=17 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to using her [[social networks]] to share information about different subjects related to the importance of preserving all forms of life, B\u00fcndchen also attended a meeting to discuss the matter at the [[United Nations Headquarters]] in [[New York City|New York]], which happened on the [[World Wildlife Day]] in 2016.<ref name = womensweardaily>{{cite web | url = https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/gisele-bundchen-joins-united-nations-wild-for-life-campaign-10438912/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | accessdate = 2 January 2020|title = Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins United Nations\u2019 \u2018Wild for Life\u2019 Campaign}}</ref> The date was celebrated with the theme \"Wildlife Future is in Our Hands.\"<ref name = womensweardaily/> She also participated in the Wild For Life campaign against the illegal trafficking of endangered wildlife, including the campaign that won the People's Choice Award in the green category of 2019 [[Webby Awards]].<ref name = wildforlife>{{cite web |url = https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/gisele-bundchen-joins-united-nations-wild-for-life-campaign-10438912/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | title =Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins United Nations\u2019 \u2018Wild for Life\u2019 Campaign | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref><ref name = webby>{{cite web |url = https://www.webbyawards.com/winners/2017/websites/general-website/green/wild-for-life/?/ | publisher = Webby Awards | title = 2017 People's Voice| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, B\u00fcndchen executive produced a [[documentary]] entitled ''Kiss the Ground''.<ref name = elledecor>{{cite web | url = https://www.elledecor.com/life-culture/a31282524/earth-day-movie-kiss-the-ground/ | publisher = Elle Decor | title = The New Film \u2018Kiss the Ground\u2019 Will Have You Doing Just That| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref> The feature focuses on a group of [[activists]], [[scientists]], [[farmers]], and politicians who band together in a global movement of \u201cRegenerative Agriculture\u201d to balance our climate, replenish our vast water supplies, and feed the world. The film features B\u00fcndchen alongside [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Ian Somerhalder]], [[Patricia Arquette]], [[David Arquette]], [[Tom Brady]], and [[Jason Mraz]].<ref name = hollywodrep>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sean-penn-drew-barrymore-spongebob-films-tribeca-2020-lineup-1282301 | publisher = Hollwood Reporter | title = Tribeca Sets World Premieres of Sean Penn Haiti Doc, Drew Barrymore Starrer 'The Stand-In' and 'SpongeBob' Sneak Peek| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref> The documentary premieres at the 2020 [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in [[New York City]] in honor of the 50th Anniversary of [[Earth Day]].<ref name = indiewir>{{cite web | url = https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/tribeca-2020-feature-lineup-1202214949/ | publisher = IndieWire | title = Tribeca 2020 Unveils Features Lineup: \u2018The Trip to Greece,\u2019 \u2018King of Staten Island,\u2019 \u2018Bad Education,\u2019 and \u2018Shirley\u2019| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Goodwill ambassador===\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen wins the 2014 UNEP Champions of the Earth Award (Personal) .png|thumb|upright|B\u00fcndchen wins the UNEP Champions of the Earth Award in 2014]]\nB\u00fcndchen and her husband, Tom Brady, served Thanksgiving dinner to more than 400 job trainees at [[Goodwill Industries | Goodwill Industries International's]] headquarters in [[Roxbury, Massachusetts]], in November 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2008/11/27/you-got-served-tom-brady-and-gisele-bundchen-dish-out-food-for-goodwill/|title=You got served! Tom Brady and Gisele Bundchen dish out food for Goodwill|last=Vanni|first=Olivia|date=November 28, 2008|website=The Boston Herald|publisher=The Boston Herald|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2009, B\u00fcndchen was designated Goodwill Ambassador for the [[United Nations Environment Programme]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?DocumentID=596&ArticleID=6315&l=en |title=Supermodel Gisele Bundchen becomes UN Environmental Ambassador |publisher=Unep.org |date=22 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20141010083051/http%3A//www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?DocumentID%3D596%26ArticleID%3D6315%26l%3Den |archivedate=10 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She made her first visit to Africa as UNEP Goodwill Ambassador in January 2012.<ref>[http://www.unep.org/newscentre/Default.aspx?DocumentID=2666&ArticleID=9004&l=en UNEP Goodwill Ambassador Gisele Bundchen Backs 'Small is Beautiful' Energy Solutions on First Mission to Africa] 13 January 2012, UNEP</ref>\n\nIn January 2012, B\u00fcndchen visited [[Kenya]] to experience the reality of energy poverty as part of the Energy for All 2030 project.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://practicalaction.org/giseleinkenya |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419081812/http://practicalaction.org/giseleinkenya |url-status=dead |archive-date=19 April 2012 |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen visits Practical Action's energy access projects in Kenya |publisher=Practicalaction.org |accessdate=24 December 2012 }}</ref> On the eve of [[World Environment Day]] in June 2012, B\u00fcndchen, planted the first of a series of 50,000 trees in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref name=\"Vega June 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/noticia/celebridades/gisele-bundchen-planta-arvore-no-rio-de-janeiro |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen planta \u00e1rvore no Rio de Janeiro |date=4 June 2012 |publisher=veja.abril.com.br |accessdate=7 June 2012}}</ref> In January 2014, B\u00fcndchen joined the [[Rainforest Alliance]] board of directors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rainforest-alliance.org/newsroom/news/gisele-bundchen-board-member |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins Rainforest Alliance Board of Directors |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104062735/http://www.rainforest-alliance.org/newsroom/news/gisele-bundchen-board-member |archivedate=4 January 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nFrom 2000 to 2005, B\u00fcndchen was in a relationship with actor [[Leonardo DiCaprio]].<ref name=USATODAY>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2019/02/01/gisele-bundchen-why-she-and-leonardo-dicaprio-broke-up/2748837002/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen finally reveals why she and Leonardo DiCaprio broke up |work=USA Today |publisher=Gannett|date=1 February 2019|access-date=1 August 2019}}</ref>  In 2004, B\u00fcndchen and DiCaprio made ''[[People (magazine)|People]]''{{'}}s annual Most Beautiful Couples List.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/gallery/0,,1046248_1051659_859203,00.html |title=Most Beautiful Couples |publisher=People.com |date=21 April 2005 |accessdate=11 January 2013}}</ref> After experiencing a period of depression, B\u00fcndchen decided to end her relationship with DiCaprio after she felt their lifestyles no longer complemented, saying in her memoir ''Lessons'', \"[...] I was becoming more and more aware of things that I\u2019d chosen not to look at. Was I alone in wanting to do some serious soul-searching while he stayed the same? In the end, unfortunately, the answer was yes.\"<ref name=USATODAY/>\n\nIn late 2006, B\u00fcndchen began dating NFL quarterback [[Tom Brady]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20009620,00.html |title=Tom Brady & Gisele Bundchen: New Couple? |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |accessdate=7 December 2012 |archivedate=6 September 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906073525/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C20009620%2C00.html |url-status=live }}</ref> after a mutual friend introduced them on a blind date.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.details.com/celebrities-entertainment/cover-stars/200907/patriots-quarterback-tom-brady-on-football-fatherhood-and-gisele-bundchen?currentPage=4|title= Patriots Quarterback Tom Brady on Football, Fatherhood, and Gisele B\u00fcndchen|accessdate=27 April 2013| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131002074606/http://www.details.com/celebrities-entertainment/cover-stars/200907/patriots-quarterback-tom-brady-on-football-fatherhood-and-gisele-bundchen?currentPage=4 | archivedate= 2 October 2013| url-status=live }}</ref> The couple married on February 26, 2009 in a small ceremony at St. Monica Catholic Church in [[Santa Monica, California]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b101983_its_true_tom_brady_gisele_buumlndchen.html|title=It's True. Tom Brady, Gisele B\u00fcndchen Secretly Wed|publisher=[[E!]]|date=27 March 2009|accessdate=12 September 2010|first=Natalie|last=Finn | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20110402182635/http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b101983_its_true_tom_brady_gisele_buumlndchen.html | archivedate=2 April 2011}}</ref> In April 2009, the couple had a second marriage ceremony, in Costa Rica.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2015/02/27/Gisele-Bundchen-shares-wedding-photo-with-Tom-Brady/1441425056291/| title=Gisele Bundchen shares wedding photo with Tom Brady: The model and NFL star married in two separate ceremonies in 2009 | first=Annie |last=Martin |agency =[[UPI]] | date=27 February 2015|accessdate=8 September 2015| archivedate= 10 March 2015 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150310113524/http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2015/02/27/Gisele-Bundchen-shares-wedding-photo-with-Tom-Brady/1441425056291/ | url-status=live}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen and Brady have two children: son Benjamin Rein (born 2009),<ref>{{cite web|url= https://people.com/parents/gisele-bundchen-and-tom-brady-name-son-benjamin/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen and Tom Brady Name Son Benjamin| work= People| publisher=Meredith Corporation|date= 18 December 2009 |accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref> and daughter Vivian Lake (born 2012).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/12/07/tom-brady-gisele-bundchen-welcome-daughter-vivian-lake/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen and Tom Brady Welcome Daughter Vivian Lake|work=People|date=7 December 2012|accessdate=7 December 2012 | first= Anya |last=Leon |first2= Charlotte |last2=Triggs | archivedate= 5 September 2015| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905100845/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/12/07/tom-brady-gisele-bundchen-welcome-daughter-vivian-lake/ | url-status=live}}</ref> She is stepmother to Brady's first son from a previous relationship with actress [[Bridget Moynahan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/celebrity/bridget-moynahan-thankful-for-healthy-baby/|title=Bridget Moynahan 'Thankful' for Healthy Baby|website=People.com|accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/celebritynews/7922407/Supermodel-Gisele-Bundchen-breastfeeding-should-be-made-law.html|title=Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen: breastfeeding should be made law|date=2 August 2010|accessdate=20 January 2010|location=London|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen practices [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-why-you-should-start-meditating|title=Why Gisele Wants You to Start Meditating|last=Plummer|first=Todd|date=May 9, 2017|website=vogue.com|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref> She and her family adhere to a primarily plant-based diet developed by their personal chef Allen Campbell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/babies/gisele-bundchen-kids-eat-plant-based-diet/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Says Her Kids Eat a (Mostly!) Plant-Based Diet: It's 'Good for Our Health' and 'the Planet'|website=People.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boston.com/sports/football/patriots/2016/01/04/meet-the-chef-who-decides-what-tom-brady-eats-and-what-definitely-doesn/gERAd0pkpmuELDZztIA56K/story.html|title=Meet the chef who decides what Tom Brady eats\u2014and what he definitely doesn\u2019t|work=Boston.com}}</ref> They have lived in [[Brookline, Massachusetts]], when Tom Brady played for the [[New England Patriots]], and reside part-time in [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/02/inside-the-multimillion-dollar-homes-of-tom-brady/#21fbabe0460f|title=Inside The Multimillion-Dollar Homes Of Tom Brady|last=Hua|first=Karen|date=2 February 2017|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=4 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811184608/https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/02/inside-the-multimillion-dollar-homes-of-tom-brady/#21fbabe0460f|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Wealth===\nIn August 2011, B\u00fcndchen ranked 60th on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of The World's 100 Most Powerful Women.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/gisele-bundchen |title=Profile |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> At age 31, she ranked third on The 20 Youngest Power Women of 2011 List.<ref>{{cite news|author=Jenna Goudreau |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jennagoudreau/2011/08/24/youngest-forbes-power-women-lady-gaga-beyonce-gisele-bundchen/ |title=The 20 Youngest Power Women of 2011 |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> In 2011, ''Forbes'' named B\u00fcndchen and Brady as the World's Highest-Paid Celebrity couple.<ref>{{cite news|last=Antunes|first=Anderson|title=The World's Highest-Paid Celebrity Couples|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2011/08/19/the-worlds-highest-paid-celebrity-couples/|publisher=Forbes.com LLC|accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref> In August 2012, B\u00fcndchen was one of four people in the fashion industry and the only model to be ranked on the ''Forbes'' list of \"The World's Most Powerful Women,\" at No. 83. She ranked eighth in the top 10 of the ''Forbes'' list of \"Entertainment's Highest-Paid Women\" in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Dorothy Pomerantz |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/10/01/oprah-tops-our-list-of-hollywoods-highest-paid-women-but-her-reign-may-soon-end/ |title=Oprah Tops Our List Of Entertainment's Highest-Paid Women, But Her Reign May Soon End |publisher=Forbes |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n''Forbes'' ranked B\u00fcndchen as the world's top-earning model for the fifth consecutive time in May 2011.<ref name=\"forbes11\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2011/05/05/top-earning-models.html?partner=relatedstoriesbox|title=The World's Top-Earning Models|last=and Steven Bertoni|first=Keren Blankfeld|date=5 May 2011|work=Forbes|accessdate=11 May 2011}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen disputed the number used by ''Forbes'', telling Brazilian website ''MdeMulher'' that the inflated estimates have made her a subject of [[audit]]ing by the [[Internal Revenue Service|IRS]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/vannale/2014/04/11/gisele-audited-by-irs-says-its-forbes-fault-i-earn-plenty-but-not-as-much-as-they-say/#1642918f302a|title=Gisele Audited By IRS, Blames Forbes: 'I Earn Plenty, But Not As Much As They Say'|publisher=Forbes|quote=I do OK, I earn plenty, but not as much as they say. I've already been audited by the IRS because of this list and, truthfully, whether I'm on this list or not doesn't interest me.}}</ref> In 2013, B\u00fcndchen ranked third on the 16 Most Successful Female Entrepreneurs list by ''Forbes''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/lml45effkg/gisele-bundchen-founder-sejaa-skincare/|title=The World's Most Powerful Female Entrepreneurs|accessdate=5 June 2013 | work=Forbes|first=Meghan|last=Casserly}}</ref> ''Forbes'' estimated B\u00fcndchen's 2016 income at $30.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/gisele-bundchen/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen |year=2016 |accessdate=16 February 2017 }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was the highest-paid model in the world from 2002\u20132017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.com/money/5033357/kendall-jenner-makes-more-than-gisele-bundchen/|title=After 15 Years, Gisele Bundchen Is No Longer the World's Highest-Paid Model|last=Calfas|first=Jennifer|date=November 21, 2017|website=money.com|publisher=Money|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]''\n| Vanessa\n| Nominated\u2014[[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Breakout Performance - Female]]<br>Nominated\u2014[[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]''\n| Serena\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n|''[[:pt:Cora\u00e7\u00e3o Vagabundo|Cora\u00e7\u00e3o Vagabundo]]''\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Herself\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Documentary\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:fr:Mademoiselle C.|Mademoiselle C.]]''\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Tom vs Time]]''\n|-\n|2020\n|''Kiss The Ground''\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[:pt:MTV al Dente|MTV al Dente]]''\n| Host\n| [[:pt:MTV al Dente|Season 3]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The O.C.]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Heavy Lifting\"\n|-\n| 2010\u201311\n| ''Gisele & the Green Team''\n| Gisele\n| Voice; also executive producer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Gisele+%26+Bob+Sinclar&titel=Heart+Of+Glass&cat=s|title=Gisele - Austrian charts| publisher=\u00d63 Austria Top 40|accessdate=18 April 2014}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Ultratip|BEL]]<br /><ref name=bel>{{cite web|url=http://www.ultratop.be/fr/song/139a18/Gisele-&-Bob-Sinclar-Heart-Of-Glass|title=Gisele Ultratop Discografie|publisher=Ultratop.be/nl/|accessdate=25 February 2012}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|FRA]]<br><ref>{{cite web | url=http://lescharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Gisele+%26+Bob+Sinclar&titel=Heart+Of+Glass&cat=s | title=Gisele & Bob Sinclar discography | publisher=Hung Medien | work=swedishcharts.com |accessdate=18 April 2014}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Media Control Charts|GER]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.offiziellecharts.de/titel-details-1284632 |title=Gisele & Bob Sinclair \u2013 'Heart of Glass'|publisher=GfK Entertainment|language=German|accessdate=5 December 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Association of Hungarian Record Companies|HUN]]<br /><ref>{{cite web|url=http://zene.slagerlistak.hu/archivum/kereso-lista-es-datum-szerint|title=Single (track) Top 20 lista - 2014. 27. h\u00e9t2014. 06. 30. - 2014. 07. 06.|publisher=Association of Hungarian Record Companies|language=German|accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"|[[OLiS|POL]]<br /><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://zpav.pl/rankingi/listy/dyskoteki/index.php?idlisty=1352 |title=Top w dyskotekach - 07 lipca - 13 lipca 2014 r. |date=30 May 2011 |publisher=[[OLiS]] |accessdate=4 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140808045536/http://zpav.pl/rankingi/listy/dyskoteki/index.php?idlisty=1352 |archivedate=8 August 2014 }}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\" | [[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|SPA]]<br><ref name=\"spn\">{{cite web | url=http://spanishcharts.com/showitem.asp?interpret=Gisele+%26+Bob+Sinclar&titel=Heart+Of+Glass&cat=s | title=Gisele & Bob Sinclar discography | publisher=Hung Medien | work=swedishcharts.com|accessdate=18 April 2014}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[Dance Club Songs|US<br>{{small|Dance}}]]<br><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/biz/charts/2013-10-05/hot-dance-club-play|title=October 5, 2013: Dance Club Songs|work=Billboard|accessdate=3 May 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[All Day and All of the Night]]\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/all-day-all-night-single/id698194689|title=All Day and All of the Night - Single by Gisele B\u00fcndchen|publisher=iTunes|date=10 April 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014 |location=London}}</ref>\n| 2013\n| \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || \u2014 || 39 \n| rowspan=\"2\" {{n/a|Non-album singles}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"[[Heart of Glass (song)#Gisele & Bob Sinclar version|Heart of Glass]]\"<ref>{{cite news|url=https://itunes.apple.com/us/album/heart-glass-radio-edit-single/id866207234|title=Heart of Glass (Radio Edit) - Single by Gisele & Bob Sinclar|publisher=iTunes|date=10 April 2014 |accessdate=11 April 2014 |location=London}}</ref><br><span style=\"font-size:85%; <!--font-weight:normal;-->\">(with [[Bob Sinclar]])</span>\n| 2014\n| 63 || 66 || 31 || 73 || 31 || 31 || 27 || \u2014 \n|-\n|align=\"center\" colspan=\"15\" style=\"font-size:8pt\"| \"\u2014\" denotes releases that did not chart or were not released in that territory.\n|}\n\n===Music videos===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|+ List of music videos, showing director\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! Year\n! Director\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| \"All Day and All of the Night\"\n| 2013\n| [[Amir Chamdin]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://chamdinstohr.se/creative/hm-fall-fashion-gisele-2013-2/ |title=H&M FALL FASHION - Gisele B\u00fcndchen - \"All Day and All of the Night\" |work=Chamdinstohr |date=13 May 2010 |accessdate=13 May 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140730002213/http://chamdinstohr.se/creative/hm-fall-fashion-gisele-2013-2/ |archivedate=30 July 2014 }}</ref>\n|-\n| scope=\"row\"| \"Heart of Glass\"\n| 2014\n| {{n/a}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Year \n! Award\n! Nominated work \n! Category \n! Result\n! Ref.\n|-\n|1998\n|Phytoervas Fashion Award\n|\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Model of the Year\n| rowspan=\"2\" {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://crisarcangeli.com/phytoervas-fashion-awards/|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171111042450/http://crisarcangeli.com/phytoervas-fashion-awards/|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 November 2017|title=Phytoervas Fashion Awards \u2013 Blog Cris Arcangeli - Beleza, bem estar, moda e muito mais!|date=11 November 2017|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|1999\n|Vh1/ Vogue Fashion Awards\n|\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.gettyimages.com/detail/news-photo/gisele-bundchen-with-her-model-of-the-year-award-at-the-vh1-news-photo/97313300#gisele-bundchen-with-her-model-of-the-year-award-at-the-vh1vogue-at-picture-id97313300|title=Gisele Bundchen with her 'Model of the Year' award at the VH|website=Gettyimages.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"|2005\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[2005 Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Awards]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]''\n|Choice Movie: Female Breakout Star\n| rowspan=\"4\" {{Nom}}\n|\n|-\n|Choice Movie: Villain\n|\n|-\n|2006\n|[[2006 Premios Juventud|Premios Juventud]]\n|\n|[[2006 Premios Juventud#Fashion and Image Category|Fashion and Image: Supermodel]]\n|\n|-\n|2007\n|[[2007 Premios Juventud|Premios Juventud]]\n|\n|[[2007 Premios Juventud#Fashion and Image Category|Fashion and Image: Supermodel]]\n|\n|-\n|2011\n|Harvard Medical School\n|\n|Global Citizen Award\n| rowspan=\"3\" {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/giseles-harvard-recognition|title=Gisele Heads To Harvard|work=Vogue|access-date=October 21, 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|2011\n|International Green Awards\n|\n|Best Green International Celebrity Award\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greenawards.com/green-awards-news/best-green-international-celebrity-award-%E2%80%93-gisele-bundchen|title=Best Green International Celebrity Award \u2013 Gisele B\u00fcndchen - International Green Awards|website=Greenawards.com|accessdate=8 January 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171120193239/http://www.greenawards.com/green-awards-news/best-green-international-celebrity-award-%E2%80%93-gisele-bundchen|archive-date=20 November 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017\n|Green Carpet Fashion Award\n|\n|Eco Laureate award\n|\n|}\n\n==See also==\n*[[List of Brazilians]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n{{Commons+cat|Gisele B\u00fcndchen|Gisele B\u00fcndchen}}\n*{{Official website|http://www.giselebundchen.com}}\n*{{Fashionmodel}}\n*{{IMDb name|1014528}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140331204652/http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Gisele_Bundchen Voguepedia]\n\n{{Navboxes\n|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen navigational boxes\n|list1=\n{{Victoria's Secret Angels}}\n{{1995\u20131999 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show models}}\n{{2000\u20132009 Victoria's Secret Fashion Show models}}\n}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{DISPLAYTITLE:Gisele B\u00fcndchen}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bundchen, Gisele}}\n[[Category:1980 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Brazilian bloggers]]\n[[Category:Brazilian expatriates in the United States]]\n[[Category:Brazilian environmentalists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian women environmentalists]]\n[[Category:Brazilian female models]]\n[[Category:Brazilian people of German descent]]\n[[Category:Brazilian models of German descent]]\n[[Category:Breastfeeding activists]]\n[[Category:Environmental bloggers]]\n[[Category:IMG Models models]]\n[[Category:People from Rio Grande do Sul]]\n[[Category:Transcendental Meditation practitioners]]\n[[Category:Victoria's Secret]]\n[[Category:Women bloggers]]\n[[Category:Twin models]]\n[[Category:Brazilian health activists]]\n[[Category:Victoria's Secret Angels]]\n", "text_old": "{{good article}}\n{{pp-pc1}}\n{{Use American English|date=August 2019}}\n{{Use MDY|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox model\n|name        = Gisele B\u00fcndchen\n|image       = Gisele Bundchen-012 (16251942066).jpg\n|caption     = B\u00fcndchen in January 2015\n|birth_name  = Gisele Caroline B\u00fcndchen<ref name=\"PF\"/>\n|birth_date  = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1980|7|20}}\n|birth_place = [[Horizontina]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Brazil]]\n|occupation={{flatlist|\n* model\n* actress\n* environmental activist\n* businesswoman\n* author\n}}\n|years_active = 1997\u2013present\n|haircolor   = {{flatlist|\n*Light brown<ref name=\"IMG Models\">Per \"Stats\" pulldown at {{cite web|title= Gisele| url=http://imgmodels.com/portfolio/new-york/women/model?mid=21993|publisher=[[IMG Models]]|accessdate=2 August 2017}}</ref>}}\n|eyecolor    = {{flatlist|\n*Blue<ref name=\"IMG Models\" />}}\n|height      = {{height|m=1.80}}<ref name=\"IMG Models\"/>\n|agency      = [[IMG Models]] (Worldwide)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.imgmodels.com/gisele/sydney/women/portfolio|title=Gisele: IMG Models|website=Imgmodels.com|accessdate=27 January 2018}}</ref><br/>Model Management (Hamburg)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://models.com/models/Gisele-Bundchen|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen - Model|website=Models.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n|website     =\n|spouse      = {{Marriage|[[Tom Brady]]|2009}}\n|children    = 2\n}}\n'''Gisele Caroline B\u00fcndchen'''<ref name=\"PF\">{{cite web|url=https://www.lofficielusa.com/fashion/gisele-bundchen-38-birthday-runway-model-moments |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen's Most Iconic Catwalk Moments|publisher=[[L'Officiel]] }}</ref> ({{IPA-pt|\u0292i\u02c8z\u025bli \u02c8b\u0129t\u0283\u1ebd|br}}, {{IPA-de|\u02c8b\u028fnt\u00e7n\u0329|lang}}, born 20 July 1980)<ref name=\"dw2006\">{{Cite news|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: \"Brazil Should Become World Champion\" |url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,,2029705,00.html |publisher=[[Deutsche Welle]] |date=27 May 2006 |accessdate=3 March 2011 |quote=Gisele B\u00fcndchen was born&nbsp;\u2013 together with her twin sister Patricia&nbsp;\u2013 on 20 July 1980 in Brazil |archivedate=29 May 2006 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20060529012721/http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0%2C%2C2029705%2C00.html |url-status=live }}</ref> is a Brazilian model, environmental activist, author, actress, and businesswoman.\n\nSince 2001, B\u00fcndchen has been one of the highest-paid models in the world.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/gisele-bundchen-forbes-names-richest-supermodel/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: First Billionaire Supermodel?|work=People}}</ref> In 2007, she was the 16th richest woman in the entertainment industry,<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2007/01/17/richest-women-entertainment-tech-media-cz_lg_richwomen07_0118womenstars_lander.html |title=The 20 Richest Women In Entertainment |work=Forbes |date=18 January 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |first1=Lea |last1=Goldman |first2=Kiri |last2=Blakeley}}</ref> and earned the top spot on ''[[Forbes]]'' top-earning models list in 2012.<ref name=BundchenEarnings2012>{{cite news |first= Brian |last=Solomon |title=The World's Highest Paid Models |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/briansolomon/2012/06/14/the-worlds-highest-paid-models/|website=Forbes.com|date=14 June 2012 |accessdate=20 June 2012}}</ref> In 2014, B\u00fcndchen was listed as the 89th Most Powerful Woman in the World by ''Forbes''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eikf45ehhi/gisele-bundchen-3/|title=World's Most Powerful Women in Media and Entertainment 2014: No. 89. Gisele Bundchen|work=Forbes}}</ref>\n\n''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]'' has credited B\u00fcndchen with ending the [[heroin chic]] era of modeling in 1999; instead ushering in a [[Sexual attraction|sexy]], healthy look with curves and a golden tan.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.vogue.it/en/magazine/editor-s-blog/2014/08/august-8th|title=Gisele Bundchen - Vogue.it|access-date=2018-03-28|language=it}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was a [[Victoria's Secret#Victoria's Secret Angels|Victoria's Secret Angel]] from 2000 until mid-2007 and had signed Victoria's Secret's  biggest contract to date. She is credited with pioneering and popularizing the \"horse walk,\" a stomping movement created by a model lifting her knees high and kicking her feet to step.<ref name=\"O'Connell\">{{cite news |url=https://www.wsj.com/public/article/SB120597258876350391.html?mod=2_1356_topbox |title=How to Walk Like a Model |last=O'Connell |first=Vanessa |date=20 March 2008 |work=The Wall Street Journal |publisher=Dow Jones & Company, Inc |accessdate=20 February 2011}}</ref> In 2007, [[Claudia Schiffer]] called B\u00fcndchen the only remaining [[supermodel]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/death-of-the-supermodel|title=\"Supermodels like we once were don't exist any more\"|website=Vogue.co.uk |date=4 September 2007 |accessdate=21 October 2019|df=dmy }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen has appeared on more than 1,200 magazine covers.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Style File |url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/gallery/gisele-style-file |publisher=Vogue |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen was nominated for Choice Movie Female Breakout Star and for Choice Movie Villain at the 2005 [[Teen Choice Awards]] for her supporting role in ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]'' (2004).<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.washingtontimes.com/multimedia/collection/richest-supermodels/?page=19|title=Beauty and Bucks: Richest Supermodels|publisher=[[The Washington Times]]}}</ref> She had a supporting role in ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]'' (2006)<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.tvguide.com/movies/the-devil-wears-prada/cast/280965/|title=The Devil Wears Prada|last=|first=|date=|website=tvguide.com|access-date=October 25, 2019}}</ref> and was the executive producer of an educational environmental cartoon, ''Gisele & the Green Team,'' in 2010 to 2011.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.latimes.com/archives/la-xpm-2010-dec-12-la-ig-gisele-20101212-story.html|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen talks about modeling, her family and \u2018Gisele & the Green Team\u2019|publisher=Los Angeles Times}}</ref>\nIn 2016, she appeared in the Emmy award-winning documentary series Years of Living Dangerously, in the episode Fueling the Fire, sharing the episode with Arnold Schwarzenegger.<ref name=\"natgeo\">{{cite web|url=https://www.natgeotv.com/za/shows/natgeo/years-of-living-dangerously|title=Years of Living Dangerously|last=|first=|date=|website=National Geographic|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=13 December 2019}}</ref>\nB\u00fcndchen's charitable endeavors include [[Save the Children]], [[International Red Cross and Red Crescent Movement|Red Cross]] and [[M\u00e9decins Sans Fronti\u00e8res|Doctors Without Borders]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nbcnewyork.com/blogs/threadny/Gisele-Ups-Brangelina-By-Giving-15-Million-to-the-Red-Cross-81759532.html|title=Report: Gisele Ups Brangelina By Giving $1.5 Million to the Red Cross|work=[[NBC]] New York}}</ref> She has been a [[Goodwill Ambassador]] for the [[United Nations Environment Program]] since 2009.<ref>{{cite news\n|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2009/09/21/bundchen_the_environmentalist/\n|work=Boston Globe\n|title=Bundchen the environmentalist\n|date=21 September 2009\n|first1=Mark\n|last1=Shanahan\n|first2=Meredith\n|last2=Goldstein}}</ref>\n\n==Family and early life==\nB\u00fcndchen is a [[German Brazilians|Brazilian of German descent]].<ref name=\"dw-world.de\">{{cite web | title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: \"Brazil Should Become World Champion\" | work=Carlos Albuquerque | url=http://www.dw-world.de/dw/article/0,2144,2029705,00.html | accessdate=23 January 2008}}</ref> Born to V\u00e2nia ([[n\u00e9e]] Nonnenmacher), a bank clerk pensioner, and Valdir B\u00fcndchen, a sociologist and writer, in [[Horizontina]], [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Southern Brazil]]<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.dw.com/pt-br/gisele-b\u00fcndchen-fala-sobre-futebol-e-suas-ra\u00edzes-alem\u00e3s/a-2028192 | title=Deutsche Welle: Gisele B\u00fcndchen fala sobre futebol e suas ra\u00edzes alem\u00e3s (in Portuguese) }}</ref> and raised in [[Rio Grande do Sul]], [[Southern Brazil]].<ref>{{cite web|last=Bennetts |first=Leslie |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/features/2009/05/gisele-bundchen200905 |title=And God Created Gisele |work=Vanity Fair |accessdate=22 November 2012}}</ref> She grew up with five sisters, Raquel, Graziela, Gabriela, Rafaela and her [[Twin#Dizygotic twins|fraternal twin]], Patr\u00edcia.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/celebrity/celebs-twin-siblings/ |title=Seeing Double: Celebs Who Have a Twin |publisher=People }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen learned German in school, but said she forgot the language after being out of touch with it.<ref name=\"dw-world.de\"/> In addition to Portuguese and English, B\u00fcndchen speaks Spanish and some French.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/features/gisele-b-ndchen-business-model-it-takes-more-than-just-good-looks-to-get-to-the-top-8782676.html|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Business model - it takes more than just good looks|date=23 August 2013|website=Independent.co.uk|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen aspired to be a [[volleyball]] player but joined a modeling course with her sisters Patr\u00edcia and Gabriela at their mother's insistence in 1993, in hopes to correct her bad posture.<ref name=\"WSJ\">{{cite web|url=https://www.wsj.com/articles/before-stardom-gisele-bundchen-thought-of-herself-as-strange-looking-11546445827?|title=Before Stardom, Gisele B\u00fcndchen Thought of Herself as \u2018Strange Looking\u2019|author=[[Marc Myers]]|publisher=[[The Wall Street Journal]]|date=3 January 2019|accessdate=7 January 2019}}</ref> The following year, she was discovered by [[Elite Model Management]] at a shopping mall in [[S\u00e3o Paulo]].<ref name=WSJ/> B\u00fcndchen was selected for a national contest, [[Elite Model Look]] (then known as Look of the Year), in which she placed second. In early 1995, at age 14, B\u00fcndchen moved to S\u00e3o Paulo to launch her modeling career. She had her first break in 1996, at [[New York Fashion Week]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/gisele-bndchen-confirms-shes-retiring-runway/story?id=30289967|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Confirms She's Retiring From the Runway|work=ABC News|last=Rothman|first=Michael|date=April 15, 2015}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===1997\u20132000: Career beginnings===\nB\u00fcndchen traveled to London in 1997, where she auditioned for 43 shows, but took part in only two international shows.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a36021/gisele-bundchen-faced-42-rejections-before-landing-first-job/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Was Rejected 42 Times Before Landing Her First Major Job|publisher=Elle}}</ref> [[Alexander McQueen]] chose her for his Spring 1998 ready-to-wear show, \"Rain!\", because of her ability to walk in towering heels on a slippery runway.<ref name=VogueJuly2018/> In 1998, B\u00fcndchen posed for [[Missoni]], [[Chlo\u00e9]], [[Dolce & Gabbana]], [[Valentino (fashion house)|Valentino]], [[Gianfranco Ferr\u00e9]], [[Ralph Lauren]], and [[Versace]] campaigns.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2016/05/15/fashion/gisele-bundchen-model-supermodel.html|title=Gisele Inc.|work=New York Times|last=Trebay|first=Guy|date=May 14, 2016|access-date=October 23, 2019}}</ref> She appeared on the cover of ''[[Vogue Paris]]'', her first cover of ''British Vogue'',<ref name=NYMag/> and ''[[i-D]]'', which featured her on its cover, profiling \"A Girl Called Gisele.\"<ref name=\"vogue.com\">{{cite web |last=Sullivan |first=Robert |url=http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Gisele_Bundchen#cite_note-3 |title=Profile |website=Vogue.com |accessdate=7 January 2013 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140331204652/http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Gisele_Bundchen#cite_note-3 |archive-date=31 March 2014 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> In 1999, B\u00fcndchen left Elite Model Management to switch to [[IMG Models]], dissatisfied with Elite's work environment.<ref name=Somethingaboutgisele>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2004/10/gisele-bundchen-fashion-film-debut|title=THERE\u2019S SOMETHING ABOUT GISELE|work=Vanity Fair|last=Andrews|first=Suzanna|date=October 2004}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to her first American ''Vogue'' cover in July 1999, dubbed \"the return of the ''sexy'' model\",<ref name=VogueJuly2018/><!--the cover stylizes it this way--> she appeared on her first group ''Vogue'' cover with fellow supermodels [[Kate Moss]], [[Amber Valletta]], [[Christy Turlington]], [[Iman (model)|Iman]], [[Lauren Hutton]], [[Naomi Campbell]], [[Stephanie Seymour]], Claudia Schiffer, [[Lisa Taylor (model)|Lisa Taylor]], [[Paulina Porizkova]], [[Carolyn Murphy]], and [[Patti Hansen]].<ref name=Gangsallhere>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/slideshow/the-gangs-all-here-7-iconic-group-model-vogue-covers-photos|title=Photos: The Gang's All Here: 7 Iconic Group Model Vogue Covers|work=Vogue}}</ref> In December of that year, she once again appeared on a solo American ''Vogue'' cover.<ref name=VogueJuly2018>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-vogue-cover-july-2018-issue?verso=true|title=Can Gisele Save the Planet?|work=Vogue|last=Haskell|first=Rob|date=June 14, 2018}}</ref> She won the [[VH1]]/''Vogue'' Model of the Year for 1999.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessinsider.com/gisele-bndchen-biography-2012-6|title=IN PICTURES: The Incredible Life Of Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen|work=Business Insider|last=Epstein|first=Eli|date=June 15, 2012}}</ref> Noting B\u00fcndchen was shooting five major campaigns at the age of 18, ''[[New York (magazine)|New York]]'' magazine editor Sally Singer said B\u00fcndchen was so successful in the industry that she deemed her an \"\u00fcber- (not super-) model.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://nymag.com/nymetro/shopping/fashion/features/864/|title=Fashion Moment|work=New York Magazine|last=Singer|first=Sally|date=May 10, 1999}}</ref> She became the fourth model to appear on the cover of ''[[Rolling Stone]]'' magazine when she was named \"The Most Beautiful Girl in the World\" in 2000.<ref>{{cite web|title=The Most Beautiful Girl|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/culture/culture-news/hot-girl-gisele-bundchen-183901/|accessdate=October 22, 2019|work=Rolling Stone}}</ref> The same year, ''[[Vogue (magazine)|Vogue]]''{{'}}s online encyclopedia of models called B\u00fcndchen the world's hottest model and said she opened a new category: the Brazilian bombshell.<ref name=\"vogue.com\"/>\n\n===2000\u20132009: Modeling breakthrough, international success, and acting debut===\nIn 2000, B\u00fcndchen appeared on 37 international ''Vogue'' covers, including three in the American edition.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.fashionmodeldirectory.com/models/gisele_bundchen/covers/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Covers|work=[[Fashion Model Directory]]}}</ref> In January 2000, B\u00fcndchen was simultaneously featured on the covers of the U.S. and British editions of ''Vogue''.<ref name=BritishVogue/> The June issue co-starred [[George Clooney]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://archive.vogue.com/issue/20000601|title=June 2000|work=Vogue Archive}}</ref> For spring 2000 fashion week, she opened shows for [[Marc Jacobs]], [[Michael Kors]], Dolce & Gabbana, [[Christian Dior]], and [[Valentino (fashion house)|Valentino]] in New York, Milan and Paris.<ref name=BritishVogue>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gisele-bundchen-biography|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Biography|work=British Vogue}}</ref> From 1998\u20132003, B\u00fcndchen was in every Dolce & Gabbana fashion campaign, totaling 11 consecutive campaigns with the brand; she returned as the face of the brand's fragrance \"The One\", in campaigns from 2006 to 2009.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.businessoffashion.com/community/people/gisele-bundchen|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen|publisher=Business of Fashion}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen retired from the runway upon signing a lucrative contract with Victoria's Secret.<ref name=Somethingaboutgisele/> In 2000, B\u00fcndchen wore Victoria's Secret's Fantasy bra, the Red Hot Fantasy Bra, worth $15 million and listed in ''Guinness World Records'' as the most expensive lingerie ever created.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.eonline.com/photos/25957/2018-victoria-s-secret-fashion-show-by-the-numbers/885016|title=2018 VICTORIA'S SECRET FASHION SHOW BY THE NUMBERS|work=E! Online}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen also modeled the \"Sexy Splendor Fantasy Bra\" in 2005, which was the second-most expensive bra ever made, valued at $12.5 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/fashion/g29045/gisele-fantasy-bra-2005/|title=Enjoy The Wonderment Of Gisele Discovering Her 2005 Fantasy Bra|work=Elle|last=Holmes|first=Sally|date=October 27, 2016}}</ref> In 2004, she appeared on another group American ''Vogue'' cover, with [[Daria Werbowy]], [[Natalia Vodianova]], [[Isabeli Fontana]], [[Karolina Kurkova]], [[Liya Kebede]], [[Hana Soukupova]], [[Gemma Ward]], and [[Karen Elson]].<ref name=Gangsallhere/> B\u00fcndchen has appeared on the covers of ''[[W (magazine)|W]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wmagazine.com/gallery/gisele-bundchen-w-covers|title=A Tribute to Gisele B\u00fcndchen, 12-Time W Magazine Cover Star|work=W|date=July 20, 2018}}</ref> ''[[Allure (magazine)|Allure]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.allure.com/gallery/gisele-bundchen-through-the-years|title=Happy Birthday, Gisele: Her Best Looks of All Time|work=Allure|date=July 20, 2015|quote=On Allure's December 2000 cover}}</ref> ''[[GQ]]'',<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.gq.com/story/gisele-bundchen-gossip-girl|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Gossip Girl|work=GQ|date=June 1, 2008}}</ref> ''[[Forbes]]'', ''[[Marie Claire]]'', ''[[Time (magazine)|TIME]]'', ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]'', ''[[Esquire (magazine)|Esquire]]'', and in the ''[[Pirelli Calendar]]''.<ref name=IMG>{{cite web|url=https://www.imgmodels.com/gisele|title=Gisele Bio|work=IMG Models}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/pirelli-calendar-photos-gisele-bundchen-cindy-crawford?verso=true|title=Exclusive: See Rare Pirelli Calendar Photos on Display at New York Fashion Week|work=Vogue}}</ref>\n\nIn acting roles, B\u00fcndchen co-starred with [[Queen Latifah]] and [[Jimmy Fallon]] in the 2004 remake of ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]'' and in 2006, B\u00fcndchen played Serena in ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen's Career Highlights |url=https://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/ |publisher=New York Mag |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was chosen by ''Time'' magazine in 2007, as one of the 100 Most Influential People in the World. In September 2007, B\u00fcndchen was photographed by [[Mario Testino]] for the cover of ''Vanity Fair''{{'}}s style issue.<ref name=NYMag>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141203055411/http://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/|archive-date=3 December 2014|url=https://nymag.com/fashion/models/gbundchen/giselebundchen/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Model Profile|work=New York Magazine|access-date=22 October 2019|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n''Forbes'' listed her 53rd on their 2007 list of the most powerful celebrities.<ref>{{cite news |title=#53 Gisele Bundchen |url=https://www.forbes.com/lists/2007/53/07celebrities_Gisele-Bundchen_2VPP.html |work=Forbes |date=14 June 2007 |accessdate=20 September 2012}}</ref> Ipanema Gisele B\u00fcndchen made an estimated [[\u00a3]]152 million (about $197 million) with more than 250 million pairs sold in 2010.<ref name=\"billionare model\">{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2011/06/02/gisele-soon-to-be-a-billionaire |title=Gisele The Billionaire |date=2 June 2011 |last=Alexander |first=Ella |accessdate=18 August 2011}}</ref> In May 2007, B\u00fcndchen had ended her contract with Victoria's Secret; she described this decision as closing that chapter of her career.<ref>{{cite web|last=Triggs |first=Charlotte |url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20037350,00.html |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen, Victoria's Secret Part Ways |work=People |date=1 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> In August 2008, the ''[[New York Daily News]]'' listed B\u00fcndchen as the fourth most powerful person in the fashion world.<ref>{{cite web |title=Photog Remembers When Nobody Liked Gisele |url=https://abcnews.go.com/blogs/entertainment/2012/10/photog-remembers-when-nobody-liked-gisele/ |publisher=abcnews.go.com |accessdate=20 January 2019}}</ref>\n\n===2009\u20132011: Continued success===\n''[[The Independent]]'' called B\u00fcndchen the biggest star in fashion history in May 2009.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/life-style/fashion/features/gisele-bndchen-the-charmed-life-of-the-megamodel-1683088.html |work=The Independent |location=London |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen: Charmed life of the mega-model |date=12 May 2009 |accessdate=3 May 2010 |quote=How did the girl from Brazil become the biggest star in fashion history?}}</ref> In April 2010, B\u00fcndchen was photographed for the cover of American ''Vogue'' for the 11th time.<ref name=\"vogue.com\" /> B\u00fcndchen closed [[Balenciaga|Balenciaga']]<nowiki/>s 2010 show in a surprise appearance.<ref name=\"vogue.com\" /><ref name=\"marieclaire1\">{{cite web |url=http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/celebrity/pictures/32510/28/rio-carnival-2011-rio-carnival-pictures-gisele-photos.html#index=9&uiSynced=true&slider=off |title=Rio Carnival pictures 2011; Gisele photos Celebrity Pictures |publisher=Marie Claire |accessdate=7 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104053222/http://www.marieclaire.co.uk/celebrity/pictures/32510/28/rio-carnival-2011-rio-carnival-pictures-gisele-photos.html#index=9&uiSynced=true&slider=off |archivedate=4 January 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She ranked third on models.com's the Money Girls list and second on the Sexiest Models list.<ref>{{cite web|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100413124529/http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?fnumber=5&lnumber=1|archive-date=April 13, 2010|url=http://models.com/rankings/money/list.html?fnumber=5&lnumber=1|title=The Money Girls are Here|website=Models.com|access-date=December 27, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> In 2011, ''CEOWorld Magazine'' ranked B\u00fcndchen among their Top Accomplished Women Entertainers.<ref>{{Cite news|title=Accomplished Women Entertainers |url=http://ceoworld.biz/ceo/2011/05/18/ceoworld-richest-women-in-entertainment-world-list-accomplished-women-entertainers |newspaper=CEOWORLD magazine |date=18 May 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160115070954/http://ceoworld.biz/ceo/2011/05/18/ceoworld-richest-women-in-entertainment-world-list-accomplished-women-entertainers |archivedate=15 January 2016 }}</ref> She was ranked No. 95 in ''[[FHM]]'' magazine's [[FHM's 100 Sexiest Women (UK)|100 Sexiest Women in the World 2011]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com/girls/100-sexiest-women |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111230002746/http://www.fhm.com/girls/100-sexiest-women |archive-date = 30 December 2011 | date=30 December 2011|title=FHM's 100 Sexiest Women in the World|work= FHM magazine}}</ref> In 2007, B\u00fcndchen was named the World's Richest Supermodel.<ref>{{cite web | url = http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20047102,00.html | title = Gisele Bundchen Named World's Richest Model | work = [[People (magazine)|People]] | accessdate =1 September 2011 }}</ref> On April 11, 2008, a black-and-white photo of B\u00fcndchen that was shot by [[Irving Penn]] was auctioned for $193,000. The picture was one of dozens from the collection of Gert Elfering that were sold at [[Christie's]] International in New York. B\u00fcndchen's picture brought the highest price.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2008/04/12/photo_of_gisele_brings_big_bucks/?p1=Well_MostPop_Emailed7 |title=Photo of Gisele brings big bucks|work=Boston Globe |date=12 April 2008 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |first1=Carol |last1=Beggy |first2=Mark |last2=Shanahan}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://exclusivo.terra.com.br/interna/0,,OI2738910-EI1118,00.html |title=\"Foto de Gisele nua \u00e9 comprada em leil\u00e3o por US$193 mile\", (Portuguese) xclusivo.terra.com.br|publisher=Exclusivo.terra.com.br |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref>\n\nBy 2010, B\u00fcndchen had appeared on two ''Vogue Shape'' issue covers, more than any other celebrity or model.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/the-past-decade-of-shape-issues/#1 |title=Shaping a Decade: Ten Years of Vogue Shape Issue |accessdate=14 February 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130419050947/http://www.vogue.com/vogue-daily/article/the-past-decade-of-shape-issues/#1 |archivedate=19 April 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She ranked No. 45 in the 2011 FHM Australia list of 100 Sexiest Women in the World.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fhm.com.au/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2011-gallery.htm |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110513014056/http://www.fhm.com.au/fhms-100-sexiest-women-in-the-world-2011-gallery.htm |url-status=dead |archive-date=13 May 2011 |title=FHM's 100 Sexiest Women in the World 2011 |accessdate=1 September 2011 }}</ref> In 2011, ''[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]'' named B\u00fcndchen as No. 25 of the 100 Hottest Women of All Time.<ref>{{cite web|title=The 100 Hottest Women of All-Time|url=http://www.menshealth.com/sex-women/hottest-women-all-time|work=[[Men's Health (magazine)|Men's Health]]|accessdate=3 January 2012|year=2011}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen closed the 2011 Givenchy spring-summer fashion show in a surprise appearance during Paris Fashion Week.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://nymag.com/daily/fashion/2011/10/gisele_bundchen_closes_out_giv.html |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Closes Out Givenchy's All-Star Show&nbsp;\u2013 The Cut |publisher=Nymag.com |date=27 December 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2013}}</ref> That year, B\u00fcndchen launched eco-friendly Sejaa Pure Skincare, a [[Cosmetics|skin care]] [[Product lining|product line]] using all-natural ingredients.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://people.com/style/gisele-bundchen-to-launch-eco-friendly-skincare-line/|title=Gisele Bundchen to Launch Eco-Friendly Skincare Line|work=People|date=2010-03-14}}</ref>\n\nShe appeared on eight ''Vogue'' covers in 2011, more than any other model or celebrity that year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fashionista.com/2011/12/this-year-in-vogue-the-covers/ |title=This Year in Vogue: An Analysis of all the Covers from 2011&nbsp;\u2013 Fashionista: Fashion Industry News, Designers, Runway Shows, Style Advice |publisher=Fashionista.com |date=8 December 2011 |accessdate=22 January 2012}}</ref> Her July ''Vogue Brasil'' 2011 cover that was shot in the [[Amazon Rainforest|Amazon]] sold 70,743 copies, making it the magazine's highest-selling issue.<ref>[http://vogue.globo.com/mundo-vogue/a-vogue-brasileira-mais-vendida-de-todos-os-tempos/ \"A Vogue brasileira mais vendida de todos os tempos\"] 10 February 2012, Brazil Vogue (in Portuguese) {{webarchive |url=https://archive.today/20120718095012/http://vogue.globo.com/mundo-vogue/a-vogue-brasileira-mais-vendida-de-todos-os-tempos/ |date=18 July 2012 }}</ref> In early 2011, Procter & Gamble's [[Pantene]] shampoo sales increased 40 percent in Latin America after B\u00fcndchen started representing the product.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2011/05/05/top-earning-models.html|title=The World's Top-Earning Models | work=Forbes | first1=Keren|last1=Blankfeld|first2=Steven|last2=Bertoni|date=5 May 2011}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u2013present: Modeling campaigns and music endeavors===\nIn spring 2012, B\u00fcndchen was featured in three spring campaigns, Versace, Givenchy, and Salvatore Ferragamo.<ref>[http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/2011/12/22/the-year-of-gisele-and-lisbeth/ \"The Year of Gisele and Lisbeth?\"] 22 December 2011, Elle {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120504023508/http://fashion.elle.com/fashion/2011/12/22/the-year-of-gisele-and-lisbeth/ |date=4 May 2012 }}</ref> She became the face of Banco do Brasil's first global ad campaign in 2012.<ref>[http://www.giselebundchen.com/novidades/10084/from-brazil-to-the-world \"From Brazil to the World\"] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120301034736/http://www.giselebundchen.com/novidades/10084/from-brazil-to-the-world |date=1 March 2012 }} News, 27 February 2012, Gisele web site</ref>\nIn April 2012, ''Time'' listed B\u00fcndchen on its All-TIME 100 Fashion Icons list, which highlighted the most influential fashion icons since 1923.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.time.com/time/specials/packages/article/0,28804,2110513_2110628,00.html |title=All-TIME 100 Fashion Icons&nbsp;\u2013 Gisele B\u00fcndchen |author=Katy Steinmetz |date=2 April 2012 |work=Time |accessdate=2 April 2012}}</ref> ''Vogue'' included B\u00fcndchen in its spotlight of the 10 women who had most appeared on its covers to honor the magazine's 120th anniversary in August 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/fashions-familiar-faces-the-women-who-have-most-often-graced-the-cover-of-vogue/#1|title=Fashion's Familiar Faces: The Women Who Have Most Often Graced the Cover of Vogue|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=19 December 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121219140203/http://www.vogue.com/magazine/article/fashions-familiar-faces-the-women-who-have-most-often-graced-the-cover-of-vogue/#1|archivedate=19 December 2012|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\n[[File:FIFA World Cup 2014 Final - Gisele B\u00fcndchen.jpg|thumb|right|268x268px|B\u00fcndchen in 2014]]\nB\u00fcndchen made 5,600 appearances in commercials in Brazil in 2012.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://revistaquem.globo.com/QUEM-News/noticia/2012/12/camila-pitanga-supera-gianecchini-e-neymar-em-campanhas-publicitarias.html|title=Camila Pitanga supera Gianecchini e Neymar em campanhas publicit\u00e1rias &#124; Quem - Not\u00edcias em QUEM News |publisher=Revistaquem.globo.com |date=27 December 2012 |accessdate=7 January 2013}}</ref> She replaced Kate Moss as the face of [[David Yurman]] in August 2012. She was photographed by [[Peter Lindbergh]] for the fall 2012 campaign.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.huffingtonpost.com/2012/08/26/kate-moss-david-yurman-gisele-bundchen-2012_n_1831200.html |title=Kate Moss Reportedly Replaced By Gisele Bundchen As The Face Of David Yurman |publisher=The Huffington Post |date=26 August 2012 |accessdate=4 February 2013 |first=Rebecca |last=Adams}}</ref> By 2012, B\u00fcndchen had appeared on 120 ''Vogue'' covers. She holds the record for appearing on the most ''Vogue Brasil'' covers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bustle.com/articles/125434-gisele-bundchen-covers-vogue-brazil-for-what-seems-like-the-millionth-time-photo|title=Gisele Bundchen Covers 'Vogue' Brazil For What Seems Like The Millionth Time \u2014 PHOTO|work=Bustle}}</ref>\n\nIn February 2013, B\u00fcndchen became the face of Chanel's make-up line, Les Beiges. The campaign was photographed by Mario Testino.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://fashiongonerogue.com/gisele-bundchen-lands-first-chanel-campaign-with-les-beiges-collection/ |title=GISELE BUNDCHEN LANDS FIRST CHANEL CAMPAIGN WITH \"LES BEIGES\" COLLECTION |publisher=FashionGoneRogue |date=4 February 2013 |accessdate=4 February 2013}}</ref> For Louis Vuitton's spring/summer 2014 campaign, Marc Jacobs chose B\u00fcndchen, [[Catherine Deneuve]], [[Sofia Coppola]], [[Fan Bingbing]], Caroline de Maigret and [[Edie Campbell]] as his muses.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wwd.com/media-news/fashion-memopad/portrait-of-a-lady-7319938|title=Louis Vuitton Campaign a Tribute to Marc Jacobs' Muses|date=19 December 2013}}</ref> In December 2013, B\u00fcndchen became [[Pantene]]'s ambassador, a deal worth $4 million per year.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.businesswire.com/news/home/20131227005266/en/Gisele-B%C3%BCndchen-Sizzles-Pantene%E2%80%99s-Newest-Ambassador#.Ur4176go7GV|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Sizzles as Pantene's Newest Ambassador|website=Businesswire.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://glamurama.uol.com.br/mais-um-contrato-mundial-para-gisele-bundchen-engordar-o-cofrinho/|title=Mais um contrato mundial para Gisele B\u00fcndchen engordar o cofrinho ...|website=Glamurama.uol.com.br}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen - Rio 2016 cropped (square).jpg|thumb|228x228px|B\u00fcndchen at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2016 Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]]|alt=|left]]B\u00fcndchen released a cover of [[the Kinks]] \"[[All Day and All of the Night]]\" as a contribution to H&M's 2013 charity campaign.<ref name=\"H&M\" /> She contributed to H&M's 2014 charity campaign by teaming with [[French people|French]] music producer and DJ [[Bob Sinclar]] to record a cover of [[Blondie (band)|Blondie]]'s 1979 classic \"[[Heart of Glass (song)|Heart of Glass]]\", on which she was credited as Gisele.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://video.repubblica.it/spettacoli-e-cultura/gisele-regina-dance-per-bob-sinclar-canta-in-bikini-animalier/163445/161935 |title= Gisele, regina dance per Bob Sinclar: canta in bikini animalier |publisher= [[Repubblica Radio TV|Repubblica TV]] |date= 22 April 2014\n|accessdate= 12 July 2014|language=it}}</ref> The single charted in France, Germany, Spain, Austria and Belgium.<ref name=\"H&M\">{{cite news|first= Olivia |last= Bergin |title= Gisele Bundchen to release charity single for H&M campaign |url= http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10282629/Gisele-Bundchen-to-release-charity-single-for-HandM-campaign.html |newspaper= [[The Daily Telegraph|The Telegraph]] |date= 3 September 2013 |accessdate= 12 July 2014 |location=London}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2014, B\u00fcndchen was chosen as the spokeswoman for [[Chanel No. 5]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/baz-and-gisele-take-five-7692136|title=Baz Luhrmann and Gisele B\u00fcndchen Take Five|website=Wwd.com}}</ref> Within the first quarter of 2014, B\u00fcndchen appeared on 17 international editions of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]],'' including the Brazilian, German, Italian, Canadian, Japanese and Chinese editions.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10922406/Gis-Elle-Bundchens-17-cover-marathon.html |title=Gis-Elle Bundchen's 17 cover marathon |author=Olivia Lidbury |website=telegraph.co.uk |accessdate=30 August 2015 |date=24 June 2014 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140627023228/http://fashion.telegraph.co.uk/article/TMG10922406/Gis-Elle-Bundchens-17-cover-marathon.html |archivedate=27 June 2014 }}</ref> Under Armour signed B\u00fcndchen to a multiyear deal in September 2014.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2014-09-02/under-armour-signs-model-gisele-bundchen-in-push-to-entice-women.html|title=Under Armour Signs Model Gisele in Push to Entice Women|author=Matt Townsend|work=Bloomberg.com|accessdate=29 March 2015|date=2 September 2014}}</ref> In 2014 and 2015, B\u00fcndchen appeared in more television commercial spots than any other Brazilian celebrity in the course of one year in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen lidera ranking de famosos em comerciais de TV|url=http://g1.globo.com/economia/midia-e-marketing/noticia/2016/01/gisele-bundchen-lidera-ranking-de-famosos-em-comerciais-de-tv.html|website=G1.globo.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://g1.globo.com/economia/midia-e-marketing/noticia/2014/12/gisele-bundchen-desbanca-neymar-em-ranking-de-aparicao-em-comercial.html|title=G1 - Gisele B\u00fcndchen desbanca Neymar em ranking de apari\u00e7\u00e3o em comercial|work=Midia e Marketing|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele getting ready for the Met Gala (Nino Munoz).jpg|thumb|upright|B\u00fcndchen getting ready for the Met Gala, 2017]]\n\nB\u00fcndchen was featured in the 2015 Guinness World Record book as the model who earned the most money from June 2014 to June 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele no Guiness &#91;sic&#93; Book como modelo mais bem paga do mundo|url=http://glamurama.uol.com.br/gisele-no-guiness-book-como-modelo-mais-bem-paga-do-mundo/|website=Glamura.uol.com.br|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\nB\u00fcndchen's $700 Taschen book released in celebration of her 20th year career sold out in one day.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele's $700 Book Sells Out|url=http://www.vogue.co.uk/news/2015/11/09/gisele-bundchen-taschen-book-700-sold-out|website=Vogue.co.uk|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\nBy 2015, B\u00fcndchen appeared in more than 550 ad campaigns, 2000 magazine covers, 3500 magazine editorials and 800 fashion shows.<ref>{{cite web|title=Runways - Gisele B\u00fcndchen|url=http://giselebundchen.com/highlights/desfiles/|website=Giselebundchen.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen appeared at the [[Maracan\u00e3 Stadium]] at the [[2016 Summer Olympics opening ceremony|opening ceremony]] of the [[2016 Summer Olympics|Summer Olympics]] in [[Rio de Janeiro]] on August 5, 2016.<ref>{{cite news | url=https://www.ew.com/article/2016/08/05/gisele-bundchen-olympics-opening-ceremony-rio | title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen dazzles at the Olympics Opening Ceremony in Rio | first=Breanne L. | last=Heldman | work=Entertainment Weekly | accessdate=5 August 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.harpersbazaar.com/fashion/models/news/a16703/gisele-bundchen-rio-olympics-2016/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen to Walk the 2016 Olympics Opening Ceremony|date=18 July 2016|website=Harpersbazaar.com}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen 2006.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|right|B\u00fcndchen in 2006]]\n\n''Forbes'' ranked B\u00fcndchen No. 61 on its Most Powerful Celebrities list in 2012.<ref>[https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/05/16/jennifer-lopez-tops-celebrity-100-list/ \"J.Lo's Stunning Career Reincarnation Puts Her No. 1 On The Celebrity 100\"] 16 May 2012, Forbes.</ref>\n''Forbes'' ranked her fourth on the World's Most Powerful Latino Celebrity list in May 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Anderson Antunes |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2012/05/25/the-worlds-most-powerful-latino-celebrities/2/ |title=The Worlds Most Powerful Latino Celebrities |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> In 2013, she ranked No. 5 on the ''Forbes'' 10 Most Powerful Businesswomen in Brazil''.''<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/eifl45ekgd/no-5-gisele-bundchen/|title=The 10 Most Powerful Businesswomen In Brazil|accessdate=5 June 2013 | work=Forbes|first=Anderson|last=Antunes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, B\u00fcndchen's Ipanema sandals sold about 25 million pairs annually and accounted for more than 60 percent of shoe manufacturer [[Grendene]]'s annual exports of about $250 million.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2014/01/10/brazils-newest-billionaire-has-gisele-to-thank-as-he-joins-forbes-list-of-the-worlds-richest//|title=Brazils newest billionaire has Giselle to thank as he joins Forbes list of the worlds richest|website=Forbes.com |accessdate=15 February 2014 | first=Anderson|last=Antunes}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, B\u00fcndchen signed a contract with [[Under Armour]], which is reportedly on par with the endorsement compensations of professional athletes and exceeds her former [[Victoria's Secret]] contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2014/09/03/gisele-bundchens-new-under-armour-gig-is-the-supermodels-most-profitable-yet/#70c52b134174|title=UPDATED: Gisele Bundchen's New Under Armour Gig|last=Altunes|first=Anderson|work=Forbes}}</ref> In 2016, Under Armour's CEO Kevin Plank said sales for the company's women's brand had increased because of its association with B\u00fcndchen.<ref>{{cite news|title=Under Armour is using Gisele for an aggressive expansion plan \u2014 and it should terrify Lululemon|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/under-armour-womens-business-could-beat-lululemon-2016-1|website=Businessinsider.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018, Gisele released her book called ''Lessons: My Path to a Meaningful Life'', which was a [[New York Times]] bestseller and was the best selling book for over six months in the non-fiction category in Brazil.<ref name = usatoday3>{{cite web | url = https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2018/10/02/gisele-bundchen-book-lessons-tom-brady-breast-implants-kids/1482259002/ \n| publisher = USA Today | title = From breast implants to life with Tom Brady: 5 'Lessons' from Gisele Bundchen's book| accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref><ref name = voguebook>{{cite web | url = https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-lessons-book-interview | publisher = Vogue | title = \"I Never Go a Day Without Dessert\"\u2014This and More, From Gisele B\u00fcndchen\u2019s New Book, Lessons | accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref><ref name = boston>{{cite web | url = https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2018/10/14/gisele-lessons-becomes-bestseller/MKYTB2ehYnzeYMCeyEax2N/story.html | publisher = Boston.com | title = Gisele\u2019s \u2018Lessons\u2019 becomes a bestseller| accessdate = 22 November 2019}}</ref> The proceeds from her book went to support social and environmental causes.<ref name = boston/>\n\n==Public image==\nIn September 2000, ''[[Newsweek]]'' reported on a survey conducted by Brazilian magazine Capricho, where 86 percent of Brazilian teenagers said they wanted to become fashion models. Capricho attributed the interest in modeling to B\u00fcndchen.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Year's Model|url=http://www.newsweek.com/years-model-159397|website=Newsweek.com|accessdate=1 November 2014|date=25 September 2000}}</ref>\n\nBy 2014, B\u00fcndchen was listed by ''Forbes'' as the 89th most powerful woman in the world.<ref name=Forbes14>{{cite news|title=The World's 100 Most Powerful Women|url=https://www.forbes.com/power-women/list/2/#tab:overall|website=Forbes.com|accessdate=26 June 2014}}</ref>\nForbes Brasil listed B\u00fcndchen as the No. 2 biggest Brazilian celebrity of 2015 based on media presence and influence in Brazil.<ref>{{cite web|title=This Year's Model|url=https://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320015943/http://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1|archivedate=20 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nIn a 2006 ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' survey, more than 50 percent of American stylists asked gave B\u00fcndchen the title of the best hair in Hollywood.<ref>{{cite web|title=Gisele Bundchen&nbsp;\u2013 Gisele Tops Elle Hair Poll|url=http://www.contactmusic.com/news.nsf/article/gisele%20tops%20elle%20hair%20poll_1004086  |publisher=Contactmusic.com |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> A February 2008 survey of more than 20,000 plastic surgeons in 84 countries revealed B\u00fcndchen was the celebrity most mentioned for patients having work done on their abdomens and hair, and the second-most mentioned celebrity in the breasts category.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.science20.com/newswire/celebrity_influences_on_plastic_surgery |title=Celebrity Influences on Plastic Surgery |accessdate=18 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen was second on ''[[Vanity Fair (magazine)|Vanity Fair]]''{{'}}s World's Most Beautiful poll in 2009.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vanityfair.com/online/daily/2009/04/angelina-jolie-is-the-most-beautiful-woman-in-the-world |title=Angelina Jolie Is the Most Beautiful Woman in the World|accessdate=27 December 2012}}</ref>\nIn January 2011, B\u00fcndchen's was the most desired female body on the ''14th Annual Famed Hottest Looks'' survey.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2011/01/06/gisele-bundchen-mark-wahlberg-plastic-surgery-celeb-bodies/ |publisher=Fox News |title=EXCLUSIVE: 14th Annual America's Most Wanted Celebrity Body Parts |date=6 January 2011}}</ref> In 2011, B\u00fcndchen was one of three women to make [[AskMen.com]]\u2019s annual \"Most Desirable Women\" list every year for 10 consecutive years.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2011/02/01/askmen-99-most-desirable-women-blake-lively-mila-kunis-sofia-vergara-angelina-jolie-gisele-beyonc/ |title=Who's the Most Desirable Actress in Hollywood? |publisher=Imnotobsessed.com |date=19 September 2011 |accessdate=24 December 2012 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://archive.today/20130126113338/http://www.imnotobsessed.com/2011/02/01/askmen-99-most-desirable-women-blake-lively-mila-kunis-sofia-vergara-angelina-jolie-gisele-beyonc/ |archivedate=26 January 2013 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen is ranked No. 4 on ''Forbes Brasil''{{'}}s list of the 100 most influential Brazilian celebrities.<ref>{{cite web|title=FORBES Brasil traz as 100 celebridades mais influentes do pa\u00eds em 2013|url=http://forbesbrasil.br.msn.com/blog/post-redacao.aspx?post=daaec777-6984-41d0-b444-2f2d194d4ed5#scpshrtu|website=Forbesbrasil.br.msn.com|accessdate=20 March 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140320173646/http://forbesbrasil.br.msn.com/blog/post-redacao.aspx?post=daaec777-6984-41d0-b444-2f2d194d4ed5#scpshrtu|archive-date=20 March 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\nIn May 2014, B\u00fcndchen was ranked No. 89 on ''Forbes''{{'}} 100 Most Powerful Women in the world, the only model on the list.<ref>{{cite web|title=The World's Most Powerful Women 2014 - Forbes|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/carolinehoward/2014/05/28/the-worlds-most-powerful-women-2014/|website=Forbes.com}}</ref>\nIn November 2014, ''Forbes Brasil'' ranked B\u00fcndchen fifth of the 25 biggest celebrities in Brazil, moving her up to second in 2015.<ref>{{cite web|title=25 maiores celebridades do Brasil em 2014 - Forbes Brasil |url=http://www.forbesbrasil.co/listas/15-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2014/ |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141204193653/http://www.forbesbrasil.co/listas/15-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2014/ |archivedate=4 December 2014 }}</ref><ref name=\"fashionweekdaily.com\">{{cite web|title=Stuart Weitzman's Susan Duffy, The Image Innovator - Daily Front Row|url=http://fashionweekdaily.com/stuart-weitzmans-susan-duffy-image-innovator/|website=Fashionweekdaily.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=RANKING: 25 maiores celebridades do Brasil em 2015 - Forbes Brasil|url=https://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170320015943/http://www.forbes.com.br/listas/2015/11/25-maiores-celebridades-do-brasil-em-2015/#foto1/|archivedate=20 March 2017|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n\nVogue Italia called B\u00fcndchen the \"King Midas of fashion\" in February 2012, saying companies that invest in her reap the awards of her representation.<ref>{{cite web|author=vogue.it |url=http://www.vogue.it/en/people-are-talking-about/obsession-of-the-day/2012/02/gisele-bundchen-forbes |title=Gisele the Millionaire |publisher=Vogue.it |date=22 November 2011 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> An Esprit public awareness campaign featuring B\u00fcndchen helped raise consumer awareness 9 percent in Germany and 19 percent in China.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20120321163229/http://svesty.com/index.php/fashion-news/113-gisele-bundchen-for-the-esprit-spring-summer-2012-collection 'Gisele Bundchen For The Esprit Spring Summer 2012 Collection\"] 15 March 2012, Svesty Fashion</ref>\n\nIn 2016 B\u00fcndchen participated in \u201cThe Beginning of Life\u201d [[documentary]] showing that the early years are the ones that structure the life of a person and that one of the biggest advances in [[neuroscience]] is the discovery that babies are much more than a [[genetic load]].<ref name = unicef>{{cite web | url = https://www.unicef.org/media/media_91198.html | publisher = UNICEF | title =Pioneering new film \"The Beginning of Life\" to be released across global streaming and multimedia platforms | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Philanthropy==\nSince the 2000s, B\u00fcndchen's main focus has been social and [[Human impact on the environment|environmental causes]].<ref name = nytimes/><ref name = vanity/> She has also supported the [[Breast Cancer Campaign]] to educate women on how to perform a [[Breast self-examination|breast self-exam]].<ref name = metro>{{cite web | url = https://metro.co.uk/2018/03/18/tom-brady-opens-mothers-battle-breast-cancer-really-well-7397533/ | publisher = Metro | title = Tom Brady opens up about mother\u2019s battle with breast cancer: \u2018She\u2019s doing really well\u2019| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Charitable activities===\n[[File:Gisele Bundchen with the United Nations 2010.jpg|thumb|upright=0.75|right|B\u00fcndchen traveling with the United Nations in 2010]]\n\nB\u00fcndchen donated $150,000 to Brazil's [[Fome Zero|Zero Hunger program]].<ref name=nytimes>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2003/03/30/world/brazil-s-war-on-hunger-off-to-a-slow-start.html |title=Brazil's War on Hunger Off to a Slow Start|work=New York Times |date=30 March 2003 |accessdate=21 October 2019 |first=Larry |last=Rohter}}</ref> She designed a limited necklace edition for ''[[Harper's Bazaar]]'', crafted by jewelers Gumuchian Fils, which were sold to raise money for [[St. Jude Children's Research Hospital]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.harpersbazaar.com/uk/fashion/fashion-news/news/g22264/how-gisele-spends-it/?slide=6 |title=How Gisele Spends It |work=Harpers Bazaar |date=15 July 2014 |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nAn iPod autographed by B\u00fcndchen and loaded with her personal playlist was auctioned, and proceeds were donated to [[Music Rising]], a campaign founded in 2005, to replace lost or destroyed instruments of musicians in the Gulf Coast Region after [[Hurricane Katrina|hurricane disasters]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/celebrity/gisele-bundchen/news |title=Page 1 of 1 for Gisele Bundchen Charity News |publisher=Looktothestars.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen became the face of [[American Express]]'s [[Product Red]]-affiliated card in 2006.<ref> {{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/finance/2946069/Gisele-Bundchen-signed-up-to-boost-Amex-Red-card.html|title=Gisele Bundchen signed up to boost Amex 'Red' card|publisher=The Telegraph|date=24 August 2006}}</ref> A portion of earnings from the credit card are donated to HIV/AIDS victims in Africa.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/lifestyle/2006-09/01/content_679601.htm |title=China Daily&nbsp;\u2013 Lifestyle |work=China Daily |date=1 September 2006 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref> In the same year she took part in the [[Keep a Child Alive|I am African]] fundraising campaign to make [[AIDS treatment]] accessible to all of [[Africa]].<ref name = borgen>{{cite web | url = https://www.borgenmagazine.com/gisele-bundchens-philanthropy/|publisher = Borgen magazine | title =  Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen is Super-Charitable| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref> In 2009, she appeared on 30 covers of the international issues of ''[[Elle (magazine)|Elle]]'' wearing Product Red clothing and posing with products from companies that support its mission.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashion.exposay.com/v/26819/gisele-bundchen-latest-promoter-product-red-clothing/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen To Be Latest Promoter Of (Product) Red Clothing & Products |publisher=Fashion.exposay.com |date=12 May 2011 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140903212927/http://fashion.exposay.com/v/26819/gisele-bundchen-latest-promoter-product-red-clothing/ |archivedate=3 September 2014 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.joinred.com/News/Articles/ArticleDetail/09-01-15/Elle_Magazine_Features_Gisele_for_RED.aspx |archive-url=https://archive.today/20090228195424/http://www.joinred.com/News/Articles/ArticleDetail/09-01-15/Elle_Magazine_Features_Gisele_for_RED.aspx |url-status=dead |archive-date=28 February 2009 |title=Elle Magazine Features Gisele for (RED) |publisher=Joinred.com |date=22 July 2009 |accessdate=3 June 2011}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen started The Luz Foundation in 2007, a project to empower girls and help them deal with self-esteem issues.<ref name = vanity>{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/style/2009/05/gisele-bundchen200905 |title=\u2026 And God Created Gisele|publisher=Vanity Fair |accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2008, B\u00fcndchen auctioned a collection of diamonds to benefit the Diamond Empowerment Fund, a nonprofit organization to education initiatives in countries where diamonds are a natural resource. The collection featured the Ponahalo Diamonds which were valued at $2 million to $4 million, a 6-carat diamond ring worth $120,000-$150,000 and a 3.35-carat Sabbadini diamond ring worth $15,000-$20,000.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/giseles-sale-running-bases-yes-we-khan-1784084/#/article/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/giseles-sale-running-bases-yes-we-khan-1784084?full=true|title=Gisele\u2019s Sale\u2026 Running Bases\u2026 Yes, We Khan\u2026|last=WWD staff|first=|date=|website=|publisher=Women's Wear Daily|publication-date=17 September 2008|accessdate=21 October 2019}}</ref>\nIn 2010, she donated $1.5 million to the [[Red Cross]] to aid the relief effort in [[Haiti]] after seeing the devastation done by the earthquake.<ref>{{cite news|last=Meredith Goldstein|first=Mark Shanahan|title=Gisele gives $1.5m to Haiti relief effort|url=https://www.boston.com/ae/celebrity/articles/2010/01/15/gisele_gives_15m_to_haiti_relief_effort/|accessdate=20 December 2012|newspaper=The Boston Globe|date=15 January 2010}}</ref> The donation put B\u00fcndchen tied for 14th on The Giving Back Fund's list of 30 celebrities who made the largest donations to charity in 2011.<ref>[http://www.givingback.org/Programs_Services/GivingBack30_2011.html 2011 Giving Back 30 Released in Parade Magazine & Parade.com] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120215132647/http://www.givingback.org/Programs_Services/GivingBack30_2011.html |date=15 February 2012 }} Giving Back.org</ref>\n\n2010, together with former president [[Bill Clinton]], B\u00fcndchen joined the event that partnered [[Pantene]] and the Children's Safe Drinking Water Program to provide [[clean water]] to people in need.<ref name=\"cnnnews\">{{cite web|url=https://money.cnn.com/news/newsfeeds/articles/prnewswire/MM69324.htm|title=Pantene Pro-V Announces Launch of 'Healthy Hair for Healthy Water,' First-Ever Pantene Global Cause Program|last=|first=|date=|website=|publisher=CNN Money|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|accessdate=28 December 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen and Indonesian singer-songwriter [[Anggun]] announced the kick-off of the Healthy Hair for Healthy Water program at [[Procter & Gamble|P&G]]'s reception that was held in conjunction with the 2010 [[Clinton Global Initiative]] in [[New York City]]. B\u00fcndchen also attended the Brazil Foundation's 8th Annual Gala to raise funds for fighting challenges faced by poor communities in [[Brazil]].<ref name = womenswear>{{cite web | url = https://wwd.com/eye/parties/the-brazil-foundation-heats-up-the-met-3300519/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | title = The Brazil Foundation Heats Up The Met| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen created an exclusive design for [[SIGG]] water bottles, with proceeds going to [[WaterAid|WaterCan NGO]], a humanitarian organization in [[Canada]] that provides the poorest people in the world access to [[clean water]], [[toilets]], and information on [[hygiene]].<ref name = vogueindia>{{cite web | url = https://www.vogue.in/content/5-reasons-why-you-should-care-about-eco-fashion-week | publisher = Vogue India | title = 5 reasons why you should care about Eco Fashion Week| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Environmental work===\nIn 2004, after visiting an [[Indian tribe]] at the [[Xingu peoples|Xingu]] region in [[Brazil]] and seeing firsthand the problems those communities were facing due to [[water pollution]] and [[deforestation]] B\u00fcndchen decided she had to do something to help bring attention to social and environmental issues. She advocated for the cause and through the years she has supported different projects, especially forest and water related projects in the [[Amazon rainforest|Amazon]] and [[Atlantic Rainforest]].<ref>{{cite web |last1=Bundchen |first1=Gisele |title=Bio by Patricia Bundchen, Gisele's twin sister. |url=http://giselebundchen.com/bio/ |website=Gisele Bundchen |publisher=Gisele Bundchen |accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2007, she signed a \"Hotter than I Should Be\u201d T-shirt that was auctioned on [[eBay]] for the [[World Wide Fund for Nature|World Wildlife Fund]] to support the charity's campaign to raise awareness about the causes and impacts of climate change.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.worldwildlife.org/press-releases/celebrities-say-they-re-hotter-than-they-should-be|title=Celebrities Say They're 'Hotter than They Should Be'|last=|first=|date=October 3, 2007|website=WWF|publisher=World Wildlife Fund|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen returned to her hometown of [[Horizontina]] in 2008 and with her family launched Projeto \u00c1gua Limpa (Clean Water Project), which implements sustainable environmental management and promotes the recovery of [[riparian]] vegetation and the micro basins of the [[region]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|title=United Nations Environment Programme|website=United Nations Environment Programme environment for development|publisher=United Nations|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20111223155449/http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|archivedate=December 23, 2011|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> More than one million trees were planted in B\u00fcndchen's name following her 2008 American Photo cover to promote Forests of the Future, a project to assist in the reforestation of the Brazilian [[Atlantic Forest]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.looktothestars.org/news/1453-gisele-bundchen-goes-au-naturel-for-rainforests |title=Gisele Bundchen Goes Au Naturel For Rainforests |publisher=Looktothestars.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn May 2009, B\u00fcndchen co-hosted the [[Rainforest Alliance]]'s annual gala to honor leaders in sustainability.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|title=UNEP Goodwill Ambassadors|date=23 December 2011|url-status=dead|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111223155449/http://www.unep.org/gwa/ambassadors/gisele/|archive-date=23 December 2011|accessdate=8 April 2019}}</ref> In May 2011, B\u00fcndchen was named Harvard's 2011 [[Global Environmental Citizen Award|Global Environmental Citizen]] in recognition of her eco-efforts.<ref>{{cite web|last=Zalopany |first=Chelsea |url=http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Eco_Fashion |title=Eco Fashion&nbsp;\u2013 Voguepedia |publisher=Vogue.com |accessdate=7 January 2013 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121223174633/http://www.vogue.com/voguepedia/Eco_Fashion |archivedate=23 December 2012 }}</ref> In November 2011, she was awarded Greenest Celebrity at the 2011 International Green awards at the National History Museum of London.<ref>{{cite web|author=Angie Tarantino |url=http://www.theenvironmentalblog.org/2011/12/super-model-gisele-bundchen-greenest-celebrity-award/ |title=Super model Gisele Bundchen wins greenest celebrity award |publisher=Theenvironmentalblog.org |date= |accessdate=19 December 2012 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140512223332/http://www.theenvironmentalblog.org/2011/12/super-model-gisele-bundchen-greenest-celebrity-award/ |archivedate=12 May 2014}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen donates proceeds from the sales from her [[Ipanema]] sandals to a different charity each year. Starting in 2006, B\u00fcndchen dedicated a percentage of the sales of her line of sandals to environmental projects including \u201cY Ikatu Xingu\u201d, meaning \"Save the Good Water of Xingu\", the project aimed to recover and protect springs and headwaters of the [[Xingu River]] in Brazil. In 2007 she supported [[World Wildlife Fund]] project \u201cNascentes do Brasil\u201d and \u201cDe olho nos manaciais\u201d from ISA. In 2008, the project supported was \u201cFlorestas do futuro\" from SOS Mata Atlantica, a [[reforestation]] program for recovery of [[native species]], which contributes to water conservation and [[biodiversity]]. A forest was named after her, the Gisele B\u00fcndchen Forest, where more than 25000 seedlings of 100 different tree species where planted in her honor, which recovered more than 15 [[hectares]] of Atlantic Forest. In 2011, the donation went to the Socio-Environmental Institute.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.co.uk/article/gisele-bundchen-biography|title=Gisele Bundchen|last=Milligan|first=Lauren|date=November 28, 2011|website=Vogue|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref> In 2009, she also helped the \"Tamar Project\", a research [[initiative]] and [[environmental protection]] of the five [[species]] of [[sea turtles]] along the Brazilian coast.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.elle.com/culture/celebrities/news/a18542/gisele-bundchen-looking-longingly-at-things/|title= Gisele B\u00fcndchen Looks Longingly At Baby Turtles And Other Things |work=Elle|access-date=January 2, 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2012, B\u00fcndchen planted a sapling of [[Lecythis pisonis|Sapucaia]] tree during her visit to Green Nation Fest, an event that occurs every year during the Environment Week and, that year, prior to the realization of Rio +20.<ref>{{cite web | url = https://m.diariolibre.com/actualidad/gisele-bndchen-planta-un-rbol-para-promover-da-mundial-del-medio-ambiente-IIDL338891 | title= Gisele B\u00fcndchen planta un \u00e1rbol para promover D\u00eda Mundial del Medio Ambiente | publisher = Diario Libre | accessdate = 3 April 2020}}</ref> Over the years B\u00fcndchen participated in several [[United Nations]] campaigns to fight against climate change. She participated in challenges on [[World Environment Day]] to mobilize people to take action in helping protect the forest, the wildlife, the green economy and to encourage people to reduce their [[food waste]].<ref name = globe>{{cite web | url = https://www.bostonglobe.com/lifestyle/names/2019/09/05/the-amazon-rainforest-still-fire-and-gisele-bundchen-speaking-out-about/uxMuHo0bJbDZv7ucLWBMVK/story.html | publisher = The Boston Globe | title = The Amazon rainforest is still on fire, and Gisele Bundchen is speaking out about it| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen attended Champions of the Earth and Equator Prize ceremonies multiples times.<ref name = popsug>{{cite web | url = https://www.popsugar.com/celebrity/photo-gallery/31926620/image/31942074/Gisele-B%C3%BCndchen-attended-Champions-Earth-UN-event | publisher = PopSugar | accessdate = 2 January 2020 | title =  Basketball Stars, Bikini Babes, and More of the Week's Cute Celebrity Candids}}</ref>\n\nIn 2013, B\u00fcndchen supported the [[United Nations]] campaign against food waste, [[World Environment Day#2013|THINK.EAT.SAVE.]] B\u00fcndchen and chef [[Eric Ripert]] participated in the [[Today (U.S. TV program)|Today Show]] program where they showed that it is possible to cook more efficiently.<ref name = usatoday>{{cite web | url = https://www.today.com/food/dont-waste-it-3-ways-use-roast-chicken-leftovers-4B11198371 | publisher = Today Show | title = Don't waste it! 3 ways to use roast chicken leftovers| accessdate = 28 December 2019}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen and her husband promote the [[Earth Hour]] global movement, a symbolic act promoted worldwide by the [[World Wildlife Foundation]] in which governments, [[companies]], and people demonstrate concern for the environment, turning off their lights for sixty [[minutes]].<ref name = grist>{{cite web | url = https://grist.org/article/2010-03-24-celeb-couple-awkwardly-ask-you-to-dim-lights-earth-hour/ |publisher = The Grist | title =Celeb couple awkwardly asks you to dim the lights for Earth Hour | accessdate = 1 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2014, B\u00fcndchen joined the Rainforest Alliance [[board of directors]].<ref name = rainforest>{{cite web | url = https://www.rainforest-alliance.org/press-releases/gisele-bundchen-board-member | publisher = Rainforest Alliance | title = Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins Rainforest Alliance Board of Directors| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> Later that year she attended, as a guest of honor the spring annual gala, a ceremony that recognized the industry champions that have sustainability as a priority. In 2014 B\u00fcndchen supported the SOKO + [[EGM: prevention of violence against women and girls|The United Nations Trust Fund to End Violence Against Women]] partnership to support the financial and physical security of women and girls around the world.<ref name = amsterdam>{{cite web | url = http://amsterdamftv.com/archives/32160 | title = Model Gisele B\u00fcndchen supports the project that helps eradicating violence against women and girls| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref> SOKO artisans in Kenya created a pair of handmade bracelets to raise awareness for the fund. B\u00fcndchen had her work in the defense of the environment recognized and was appointed as Goodwill Ambassador for the [[United Nations Environment Programme]] (UNEP).<ref name = parade/> Since then, B\u00fcndchen has helped UNEP in the mission of raising awareness and inspiring action to protect the environment.<ref name = parade>{{cite web | url = https://parade.com/96477/parade/gisele-bundchen-goodwill-ambassador/ | publisher = Parade | title =  Gisele Bundchen Named Goodwill Ambassador | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2016, she joined the climate change documentary show [[Years of Living Dangerously]] as one of its celebrity correspondents.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boston.com/culture/celebs/2016/06/02/gisele-shows-us-shes-earth-goddess-busy-saving-planet |title=Gisele will appear on National Geographic's 'Years of Living Dangerously' |publisher=boston.com |accessdate=17 June 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn addition to using her [[social networks]] to share information about different subjects related to the importance of preserving all forms of life, B\u00fcndchen also attended a meeting to discuss the matter at the [[United Nations Headquarters]] in [[New York City|New York]], which happened on the [[World Wildlife Day]] in 2016.<ref name = womensweardaily>{{cite web | url = https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/gisele-bundchen-joins-united-nations-wild-for-life-campaign-10438912/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | accessdate = 2 January 2020|title = Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins United Nations\u2019 \u2018Wild for Life\u2019 Campaign}}</ref> The date was celebrated with the theme \"Wildlife Future is in Our Hands.\"<ref name = womensweardaily/> She also participated in the Wild For Life campaign against the illegal trafficking of endangered wildlife, including the campaign that won the People's Choice Award in the green category of 2019 [[Webby Awards]].<ref name = wildforlife>{{cite web |url = https://wwd.com/fashion-news/fashion-scoops/gisele-bundchen-joins-united-nations-wild-for-life-campaign-10438912/ | publisher = Women's Wear Daily | title =Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins United Nations\u2019 \u2018Wild for Life\u2019 Campaign | accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref><ref name = webby>{{cite web |url = https://www.webbyawards.com/winners/2017/websites/general-website/green/wild-for-life/?/ | publisher = Webby Awards | title = 2017 People's Voice| accessdate = 2 January 2020}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, B\u00fcndchen executive produced a [[documentary]] entitled ''Kiss the Ground''.<ref name = elledecor>{{cite web | url = https://www.elledecor.com/life-culture/a31282524/earth-day-movie-kiss-the-ground/ | publisher = Elle Decor | title = The New Film \u2018Kiss the Ground\u2019 Will Have You Doing Just That| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref> The feature focuses on a group of [[activists]], [[scientists]], [[farmers]], and politicians who band together in a global movement of \u201cRegenerative Agriculture\u201d to balance our climate, replenish our vast water supplies, and feed the world. The film features B\u00fcndchen alongside [[Woody Harrelson]], [[Ian Somerhalder]], [[Patricia Arquette]], [[David Arquette]], [[Tom Brady]], and [[Jason Mraz]].<ref name = hollywodrep>{{cite web | url = https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/sean-penn-drew-barrymore-spongebob-films-tribeca-2020-lineup-1282301 | publisher = Hollwood Reporter | title = Tribeca Sets World Premieres of Sean Penn Haiti Doc, Drew Barrymore Starrer 'The Stand-In' and 'SpongeBob' Sneak Peek| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref> The documentary premieres at the 2020 [[Tribeca Film Festival]] in [[New York City]] in honor of the 50th Anniversary of [[Earth Day]].<ref name = indiewir>{{cite web | url = https://www.indiewire.com/2020/03/tribeca-2020-feature-lineup-1202214949/ | publisher = IndieWire | title = Tribeca 2020 Unveils Features Lineup: \u2018The Trip to Greece,\u2019 \u2018King of Staten Island,\u2019 \u2018Bad Education,\u2019 and \u2018Shirley\u2019| accessdate = 17 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Goodwill ambassador===\n[[File:Gisele B\u00fcndchen wins the 2014 UNEP Champions of the Earth Award (Personal) .png|thumb|upright|B\u00fcndchen wins the UNEP Champions of the Earth Award in 2014]]\nB\u00fcndchen and her husband, Tom Brady, served Thanksgiving dinner to more than 400 job trainees at [[Goodwill Industries | Goodwill Industries International's]] headquarters in [[Roxbury, Massachusetts]], in November 2008.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonherald.com/2008/11/27/you-got-served-tom-brady-and-gisele-bundchen-dish-out-food-for-goodwill/|title=You got served! Tom Brady and Gisele Bundchen dish out food for Goodwill|last=Vanni|first=Olivia|date=November 28, 2008|website=The Boston Herald|publisher=The Boston Herald|accessdate=October 22, 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn September 2009, B\u00fcndchen was designated Goodwill Ambassador for the [[United Nations Environment Programme]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?DocumentID=596&ArticleID=6315&l=en |title=Supermodel Gisele Bundchen becomes UN Environmental Ambassador |publisher=Unep.org |date=22 May 2007 |accessdate=3 June 2011 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=http://webarchive.loc.gov/all/20141010083051/http%3A//www.unep.org/Documents.Multilingual/Default.asp?DocumentID%3D596%26ArticleID%3D6315%26l%3Den |archivedate=10 October 2014 |df=dmy-all }}</ref> She made her first visit to Africa as UNEP Goodwill Ambassador in January 2012.<ref>[http://www.unep.org/newscentre/Default.aspx?DocumentID=2666&ArticleID=9004&l=en UNEP Goodwill Ambassador Gisele Bundchen Backs 'Small is Beautiful' Energy Solutions on First Mission to Africa] 13 January 2012, UNEP</ref>\n\nIn January 2012, B\u00fcndchen visited [[Kenya]] to experience the reality of energy poverty as part of the Energy for All 2030 project.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://practicalaction.org/giseleinkenya |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120419081812/http://practicalaction.org/giseleinkenya |url-status=dead |archive-date=19 April 2012 |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen visits Practical Action's energy access projects in Kenya |publisher=Practicalaction.org |accessdate=24 December 2012 }}</ref> On the eve of [[World Environment Day]] in June 2012, B\u00fcndchen, planted the first of a series of 50,000 trees in [[Rio de Janeiro]].<ref name=\"Vega June 2012\">{{cite web |url=http://veja.abril.com.br/noticia/celebridades/gisele-bundchen-planta-arvore-no-rio-de-janeiro |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen planta \u00e1rvore no Rio de Janeiro |date=4 June 2012 |publisher=veja.abril.com.br |accessdate=7 June 2012}}</ref> In January 2014, B\u00fcndchen joined the [[Rainforest Alliance]] board of directors.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rainforest-alliance.org/newsroom/news/gisele-bundchen-board-member |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Joins Rainforest Alliance Board of Directors |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140104062735/http://www.rainforest-alliance.org/newsroom/news/gisele-bundchen-board-member |archivedate=4 January 2014 }}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nFrom 2000 to 2005, B\u00fcndchen was in a relationship with actor [[Leonardo DiCaprio]].<ref name=USATODAY>{{cite web|url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/life/entertainthis/2019/02/01/gisele-bundchen-why-she-and-leonardo-dicaprio-broke-up/2748837002/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen finally reveals why she and Leonardo DiCaprio broke up |work=USA Today |publisher=Gannett|date=1 February 2019|access-date=1 August 2019}}</ref>  In 2004, B\u00fcndchen and DiCaprio made ''[[People (magazine)|People]]''{{'}}s annual Most Beautiful Couples List.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/gallery/0,,1046248_1051659_859203,00.html |title=Most Beautiful Couples |publisher=People.com |date=21 April 2005 |accessdate=11 January 2013}}</ref> After experiencing a period of depression, B\u00fcndchen decided to end her relationship with DiCaprio after she felt their lifestyles no longer complemented, saying in her memoir ''Lessons'', \"[...] I was becoming more and more aware of things that I\u2019d chosen not to look at. Was I alone in wanting to do some serious soul-searching while he stayed the same? In the end, unfortunately, the answer was yes.\"<ref name=USATODAY/>\n\nIn late 2006, B\u00fcndchen began dating NFL quarterback [[Tom Brady]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/people/article/0,,20009620,00.html |title=Tom Brady & Gisele Bundchen: New Couple? |work=[[People (magazine)|People]] |accessdate=7 December 2012 |archivedate=6 September 2015 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150906073525/http://www.people.com/people/article/0%2C%2C20009620%2C00.html |url-status=live }}</ref> after a mutual friend introduced them on a blind date.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.details.com/celebrities-entertainment/cover-stars/200907/patriots-quarterback-tom-brady-on-football-fatherhood-and-gisele-bundchen?currentPage=4|title= Patriots Quarterback Tom Brady on Football, Fatherhood, and Gisele B\u00fcndchen|accessdate=27 April 2013| archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20131002074606/http://www.details.com/celebrities-entertainment/cover-stars/200907/patriots-quarterback-tom-brady-on-football-fatherhood-and-gisele-bundchen?currentPage=4 | archivedate= 2 October 2013| url-status=live }}</ref> The couple married on February 26, 2009 in a small ceremony at St. Monica Catholic Church in [[Santa Monica, California]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b101983_its_true_tom_brady_gisele_buumlndchen.html|title=It's True. Tom Brady, Gisele B\u00fcndchen Secretly Wed|publisher=[[E!]]|date=27 March 2009|accessdate=12 September 2010|first=Natalie|last=Finn | archiveurl =https://web.archive.org/web/20110402182635/http://www.eonline.com/uberblog/b101983_its_true_tom_brady_gisele_buumlndchen.html | archivedate=2 April 2011}}</ref> In April 2009, the couple had a second marriage ceremony, in Costa Rica.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2015/02/27/Gisele-Bundchen-shares-wedding-photo-with-Tom-Brady/1441425056291/| title=Gisele Bundchen shares wedding photo with Tom Brady: The model and NFL star married in two separate ceremonies in 2009 | first=Annie |last=Martin |agency =[[UPI]] | date=27 February 2015|accessdate=8 September 2015| archivedate= 10 March 2015 | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20150310113524/http://www.upi.com/Entertainment_News/2015/02/27/Gisele-Bundchen-shares-wedding-photo-with-Tom-Brady/1441425056291/ | url-status=live}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen and Brady have two children: son Benjamin Rein (born 2009),<ref>{{cite web|url= https://people.com/parents/gisele-bundchen-and-tom-brady-name-son-benjamin/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen and Tom Brady Name Son Benjamin| work= People| publisher=Meredith Corporation|date= 18 December 2009 |accessdate=2 April 2020}}</ref> and daughter Vivian Lake (born 2012).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/12/07/tom-brady-gisele-bundchen-welcome-daughter-vivian-lake/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen and Tom Brady Welcome Daughter Vivian Lake|work=People|date=7 December 2012|accessdate=7 December 2012 | first= Anya |last=Leon |first2= Charlotte |last2=Triggs | archivedate= 5 September 2015| archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150905100845/http://celebritybabies.people.com/2012/12/07/tom-brady-gisele-bundchen-welcome-daughter-vivian-lake/ | url-status=live}}</ref> She is stepmother to Brady's first son from a previous relationship with actress [[Bridget Moynahan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/celebrity/bridget-moynahan-thankful-for-healthy-baby/|title=Bridget Moynahan 'Thankful' for Healthy Baby|website=People.com|accessdate=18 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url = https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/newstopics/celebritynews/7922407/Supermodel-Gisele-Bundchen-breastfeeding-should-be-made-law.html|title=Supermodel Gisele B\u00fcndchen: breastfeeding should be made law|date=2 August 2010|accessdate=20 January 2010|location=London|work=The Daily Telegraph}}</ref>\n\nB\u00fcndchen practices [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vogue.com/article/gisele-bundchen-why-you-should-start-meditating|title=Why Gisele Wants You to Start Meditating|last=Plummer|first=Todd|date=May 9, 2017|website=vogue.com|publisher=Vogue|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref> She and her family adhere to a primarily plant-based diet developed by their personal chef Allen Campbell.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://people.com/babies/gisele-bundchen-kids-eat-plant-based-diet/|title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen Says Her Kids Eat a (Mostly!) Plant-Based Diet: It's 'Good for Our Health' and 'the Planet'|website=People.com|accessdate=8 January 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.boston.com/sports/football/patriots/2016/01/04/meet-the-chef-who-decides-what-tom-brady-eats-and-what-definitely-doesn/gERAd0pkpmuELDZztIA56K/story.html|title=Meet the chef who decides what Tom Brady eats\u2014and what he definitely doesn\u2019t|work=Boston.com}}</ref> They have lived in [[Brookline, Massachusetts]], when Tom Brady played for the [[New England Patriots]], and reside part-time in [[New York City]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/02/inside-the-multimillion-dollar-homes-of-tom-brady/#21fbabe0460f|title=Inside The Multimillion-Dollar Homes Of Tom Brady|last=Hua|first=Karen|date=2 February 2017|work=[[Forbes]]|accessdate=4 February 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811184608/https://www.forbes.com/sites/karenhua/2017/02/02/inside-the-multimillion-dollar-homes-of-tom-brady/#21fbabe0460f|archive-date=11 August 2017|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n===Wealth===\nIn August 2011, B\u00fcndchen ranked 60th on the ''[[Forbes]]'' list of The World's 100 Most Powerful Women.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/gisele-bundchen |title=Profile |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> At age 31, she ranked third on The 20 Youngest Power Women of 2011 List.<ref>{{cite news|author=Jenna Goudreau |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/jennagoudreau/2011/08/24/youngest-forbes-power-women-lady-gaga-beyonce-gisele-bundchen/ |title=The 20 Youngest Power Women of 2011 |publisher=Forbes.com |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref> In 2011, ''Forbes'' named B\u00fcndchen and Brady as the World's Highest-Paid Celebrity couple.<ref>{{cite news|last=Antunes|first=Anderson|title=The World's Highest-Paid Celebrity Couples|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/andersonantunes/2011/08/19/the-worlds-highest-paid-celebrity-couples/|publisher=Forbes.com LLC|accessdate=13 December 2011}}</ref> In August 2012, B\u00fcndchen was one of four people in the fashion industry and the only model to be ranked on the ''Forbes'' list of \"The World's Most Powerful Women,\" at No. 83. She ranked eighth in the top 10 of the ''Forbes'' list of \"Entertainment's Highest-Paid Women\" in 2012.<ref>{{cite news|author=Dorothy Pomerantz |url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/dorothypomerantz/2012/10/01/oprah-tops-our-list-of-hollywoods-highest-paid-women-but-her-reign-may-soon-end/ |title=Oprah Tops Our List Of Entertainment's Highest-Paid Women, But Her Reign May Soon End |publisher=Forbes |date=18 April 2012 |accessdate=19 December 2012}}</ref>\n\n''Forbes'' ranked B\u00fcndchen as the world's top-earning model for the fifth consecutive time in May 2011.<ref name=\"forbes11\">{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/2011/05/05/top-earning-models.html?partner=relatedstoriesbox|title=The World's Top-Earning Models|last=and Steven Bertoni|first=Keren Blankfeld|date=5 May 2011|work=Forbes|accessdate=11 May 2011}}</ref> B\u00fcndchen disputed the number used by ''Forbes'', telling Brazilian website ''MdeMulher'' that the inflated estimates have made her a subject of [[audit]]ing by the [[Internal Revenue Service|IRS]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.forbes.com/sites/vannale/2014/04/11/gisele-audited-by-irs-says-its-forbes-fault-i-earn-plenty-but-not-as-much-as-they-say/#1642918f302a|title=Gisele Audited By IRS, Blames Forbes: 'I Earn Plenty, But Not As Much As They Say'|publisher=Forbes|quote=I do OK, I earn plenty, but not as much as they say. I've already been audited by the IRS because of this list and, truthfully, whether I'm on this list or not doesn't interest me.}}</ref> In 2013, B\u00fcndchen ranked third on the 16 Most Successful Female Entrepreneurs list by ''Forbes''.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.forbes.com/pictures/lml45effkg/gisele-bundchen-founder-sejaa-skincare/|title=The World's Most Powerful Female Entrepreneurs|accessdate=5 June 2013 | work=Forbes|first=Meghan|last=Casserly}}</ref> ''Forbes'' estimated B\u00fcndchen's 2016 income at $30.5 million.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbes.com/profile/gisele-bundchen/ |title=Gisele B\u00fcndchen |year=2016 |accessdate=16 February 2017 }}</ref> B\u00fcndchen was the highest-paid model in the world from 2002\u20132017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://money.com/money/5033357/kendall-jenner-makes-more-than-gisele-bundchen/|title=After 15 Years, Gisele Bundchen Is No Longer the World's Highest-Paid Model|last=Calfas|first=Jennifer|date=November 21, 2017|website=money.com|publisher=Money|accessdate=October 25, 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Filmography===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Film\n|-\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 2004\n| ''[[Taxi (2004 film)|Taxi]]''\n| Vanessa\n| Nominated\u2014[[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Breakout Performance - Female]]<br>Nominated\u2014[[Teen Choice Awards|Teen Choice Award for Choice Movie Villain]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The Devil Wears Prada (film)|The Devil Wears Prada]]''\n| Serena\n|\n|-\n| 2008\n|''[[:pt:Cora\u00e7\u00e3o Vagabundo|Cora\u00e7\u00e3o Vagabundo]]''\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Herself\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Documentary\n|-\n| 2013\n| ''[[:fr:Mademoiselle C.|Mademoiselle C.]]''\n|-\n|2018\n|''[[Tom vs Time]]''\n|-\n|2020\n|''Kiss The Ground''\n|}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|+ Television\n! Year\n! Title\n! Role\n! class=\"unsortable\" | Notes\n|-\n| 1996\n| ''[[:pt:MTV al Dente|MTV al Dente]]''\n| Host\n| [[:pt:MTV al Dente|Season 3]]\n|-\n| 2006\n| ''[[The O.C.]]''\n| Herself\n| Episode: \"The Heavy Lifting\"\n|-\n| 2010\u201311\n| ''Gisele & the Green Team''\n| Gisele\n| Voice; also executive producer\n|-\n|}\n\n==Discography==\n\n===Singles===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\" border=\"1\"\n|+ List of singles, with selected chart positions and certifications\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:16em;\" | Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"8\" | Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:2.5em;font-size:90%;\"| [[\u00d63 Austria Top 40|AUT]]<br><ref>{{cite web| url=http://www.austriancharts.at/showitem.asp?interpret=Gisele+%26+Bob+Sinclar&titel=Heart+Of+Glass&cat=s|title=Gisele - Austrian charts| publisher=\u00d63 Austria Top 